title: garbanzo bean soup
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, slice green onions.
Reserve 1 tablespoon green onions for garnish.
In a 4-quart saucepan, over medium heat in hot butter, cook remaining green onions until tender.

title: creamy 2-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar with an electric mixer, or wire whisk until well blended.

title: crescent roll lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add sauce and simmer. Spread one can of rolls on bottom of 9x13 pan. Pinch edges together to cover bottom of pan. Layer meat mixture then cheeses and top with remaining can of rolls. Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: italian chicken soup
directions: Cover the chicken in water and boil until tender.
Debone chicken and return the meat to the broth.
Add dry onion soup mix, tomatoes, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Return to boil, then add macaroni twirls.
Cook until macaroni twirls are tender. Serve.

title: quick and tasty peanut butter pie
directions: Open Cool Whip.
Spoon in peanut butter; mix on high speed until stiff.
Spread into crust and chill.

title: quick bran loaf
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder together.
Stir in wheat bran and raisins.
Beat egg and sugar together; add molasses, sour milk and melted shortening.
Stir into flour mixture.
Bake in greased bread pan at 350° for about an hour.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Mix rice, soups and water.
Spread over bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Lay chicken parts on top; sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
If using glass dish, heat oven to 325°.

title: triple chocolate chip
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple cake in a pie tin(yummy!)
directions: Add sugar to well beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients, apples, nuts and vanilla all at once.
Stir all together.
Bake in greased pie tin at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: layered salad
directions: Put chopped lettuce in large bowl.
Add a layer of all peas. Combine onion, celery and green pepper and let that be your next layer.
Spread on mayonnaise and sprinkle with sugar.
Add a layer of cheese and put crumbled bacon on top.
Cover and let refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Toss just before serving.

title: fluffy squash souffle
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water until tender. Drain and cool. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Add sugar and cheese. Place in a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter. Sprinkle with black pepper and paprika. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hershey's great american chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Then put the flour, baking soda, salt, chocolate chips and chopped nuts if wanted.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Use a big salad bowl.
Make in order given in layers.
Do not mix.
Make at least one day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.
Stays very crisp.
Toss before serving.
Serves about 28.

title: very good sugar cookies
directions: Mix and chill.
Then roll into balls and dip in sugar. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not let brown.

title: fettucine with olive sauce
directions: Cook fettucine and keep warm.
Heat olive oil and cook garlic until it begins to brown.
Stir in olives, parsley, oregano, red pepper and 1/2 cup water over high heat just to boiling; stir occasionally.
Stir olive mixture into fettucine in saucepot.
Add cheese and toss until well mixed.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: pasta with tomato and basil sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, cook garlic in olive oil, about 1 minute. Add all ingredients.
Cook over low heat until boiling, stirring occasionally.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook pasta; drain. Pour sauce over; garnish with cheese.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Serve in large glass bowl for pretty effect.
Chill several hours.

title: 6 cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit and mix with other ingredients.
Chill overnight, if possible before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together in mixer.
Bake in two 9-inch pie shells at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease	and
flour rectangular cake pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom.	Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour on top of	nuts
and coconut.
Mix margarine and cream cheese together. Add
powdered
sugar.
Pour
mixture over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in buttered baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.
You may substitute peaches for apples in this recipe.
Serves 6.
(Easy and good.)

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and melt; crumble in sausage and Bisquick mix. Shape into small balls and bake on ungreased baking sheet for 20 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a large kettle, cook ground meat, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water and add other ingredients in order listed; congeal.

title: eddie's tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion and celery until tender. Add remaining ingredients and cook about 15 to 20 minutes so flavors blend.
Makes 1 1/2 cups of the barbecue sauce.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. Place in a deep baking dish. Combine cake mix, sugar, cinnamon, butter and nuts in a separate bowl. Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle mixture evenly over apples. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender at 350°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into the lukewarm water.
Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and shortening; cool until lukewarm.
Then add yeast and beaten eggs; mix well.
Add about 4 or 5 cups of flour. Beat thoroughly, then add 2 to 3 cups of flour and knead (with hands) until the flour is worked into the dough.
Place in a greased mixing bowl; cover well with heavy wax paper and place in refrigerator.
After 2 hours, take out and allow to double in size in warm place.
Knead down and let rise again.
Make rolls by hand and place on greased cookie sheet.
Allow to rise for 1 hour. Bake at 350° until done.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add cream cheese and beat until fluffy.
Add flour and eggs, alternating, starting and ending with flour.
Stir in flavoring.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook hamburger and onion flakes in skillet.
Drain.
Mix together hamburger mixture, corn, 3/4 cup cheese and tomato sauce. Stuff well washed peppers with mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Put in crock-pot.
Add 1/3 cup water.
Cook on low for 7 to 10 hours and on high for 4 to 7 hours.

title: tomato and rice soup
directions: Cook rice and celery in chicken broth until rice is tender. Add tomato soup and salt to taste.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions; drain and set aside to cool.
Combine celery, onion, pepper and vegetables to drained, rinsed kidney beans.
Mix well.
In a saucepan, mix vinegar, mustard, sugar and flour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until clear and thick.
Cool and fold into vegetable mix.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Beat egg yolks well. Add cream, butter, Fruit Sweet and vanilla and beat to blend well. Set aside. Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together and set aside in a small bowl. In a medium bowl, slowly blend the flour mixture and the liquid mixture in

small amounts at a time until well mixed. Beat until smooth. In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Stir a third of the whites into the batter and then gently fold in the reminder. Spoon into a greased and floured 9 inch pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25-35 minutes or until an inserted straw or toothpick comes out dry. Cool for about 5 minutes before turning out onto rack.

title: beef stroganoff nerelli
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Brown meat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer until tender.
Combine mushrooms and onions.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: high protein breakfast bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; then cut in margarine until mixture is coarse crumbs.
Stir in oats, cheese, bacon and raisins.
Add milk and mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spread into a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars. Can be wrapped individually and frozen.
Great snack or lunch box treats.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix and put in freezer.

title: tuna layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, shells, cucumber, tomatoes, tuna, peas and cheese in 3-quart serving bowl.
Spread Miracle Whip salad dressing over salad sealing to edge of bowl; cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss to serve.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and put in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Flake crabmeat.
If using canned crabmeat, drain and remove cartilage, then flake.
In 1/4 cup hot butter in medium size skillet, cook onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add bread crumbs, mixing well.
Add crumb mixture to crabmeat along with eggs, salt, mustard, parsley and cream; mix well.
Shape mixture into 8 thick patties about 2 1/2-inches in diameter.
Coat with flour.
Heat remaining butter in large skillet.
Add patties and saute until golden on both sides.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in grated apples.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, milk and vanilla.
Add to creamed mixture.
Pour in a greased and floured loaf pan; let set 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.

title: aunt petsy's santa cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and orange rind.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and beat until smooth.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll out thin.
Use cookie cutters.
Bake in a 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not brown!

title: peanut butter balls(rice krispies)
directions: Mix ingredients together, except chocolate.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts or smaller.
Dip into melted chocolate.
Cool on Saran Wrap or tinfoil.
Raisins or chopped nuts may be added.

title: coffee floating island
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix, sugar, coffee and salt.
Slowly beat with mixer until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into serving bowl or individual dishes.
Chill and let stand to set.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Combine 2 cups sugar, oil and eggs; beat well. Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk. Stir in coconut and 2 teaspoons coconut extract. Bake at 325° for 65 minutes in greased tube pan.

title: corn-on-the-cob and chicken dinner
directions: In a Dutch oven melt butter; add chicken and garlic.
Cook over high heat, stirring occasionally, until chicken is golden brown (10 to 15 minutes).
Reduce heat to medium.
Add remaining ingredients except zucchini and tomatoes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in half.
Place in saucepan.
Cover with boiling water.
Cover pan and cook until tender when pierced with fork, about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Shake pan over low heat a few minutes to dry potatoes.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Dice and cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon on paper towels.
Return 6 tablespoons of drippings to skillet.
Add onions; cook, stirring frequently, until transparent.
Stir in vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add bacon and stir.
Pour over potatoes. Toss lightly to distribute bacon.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon souffle cheesecake
directions: Spray an 8-inch or 9-inch spring form pan or 9-inch pie plate with non-stick cooking spray. Sprinkle 1 Tbsp. graham cracker crumbs on the sides of the pan; set aside. Place the gelatin in a medium bowl. Stir in the boiling water until the gelatin is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes. Pour the mixture into a blender or food processor fitted with the metal blade. Add cottage cheese and cream cheese. Blend or process on medium speed until smooth.

Pour the mixture into a large bowl and fold in the whipped topping to completely incorporate. Pour the mixture into a prepared pan and smooth top. Sprinkle the remaining 1 Tbsp. graham cracker crumbs around the outside edge. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Remove side of pan just before serving.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet until brown; drain grease.
Mix with other ingredients and cook very slowly, 1 to 2 hours.
Green pepper and celery can be added.
Water can be added if liquid cooks away.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and keep refrigerated.

title: mom's "sunshine cake"(sponge)
directions: Separate eggs; put yolks in medium bowl, whites in large.
Beat egg yolks until blended.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, gradually, beating constantly.
Combine lemon juice, rind and water and add gradually to yolks, beating until fluffy, light and very thick.
Add flour all at once and fold in gently until just blended.
Wash beater, then beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until whites just form moist peaks.
Add 1/2 cup sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Turn yolk mixture onto beaten whites and gently fold together until no streaks of yolks or whites.
Turn into ungreased 9-inch tube pan.
Cut through batter with spatula to remove air bubbles.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let pan rest on tube or side supports until cool.

title: wild rice soup(6 generous servings)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly.
Stir in rice and salt; simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend in half and half and sherry.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to serving temperature, but do not boil.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Cook syrup until clear.
Keep warm while peeling peaches.
Pack jar with 1/2 stick cinnamon and 4 to 5 whole cloves for each quart if you do not can peaches whole.
(I halve mine.)
Process in hot water bath for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
6 quarts or 12 pints.

title: new orleans shrimp
directions: Marinate shrimp overnight in mixture.
Serve as appetizer.

title: crock pot roast
directions: Place potatoes, carrots, celery and onions in Crock Pot. Trim fat and place roast on top.
Mix tomatoes and water; pour over roast.
Covered and cook on low for 11-12 hours.
Serves 3-5 people.

title: fruit delight
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Drain mixed fruit, do not save juice.
Mix pineapple and fruit mix with Tang.
Add pudding mix. Mix well.
Slice bananas in pineapple juice.
Add to fruit mixture and mix again.

title: baked fish with orange sauce(venezuelan dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Rub fish with lemon, cut in half; rinse.
In a blender or food processor, pour the orange juice, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Add salt, pepper, ketchup, pimiento, paprika, onion and the oil.
Blend well and pour it over fish.
Once the fish is all covered with the sauce, put everything in an oven pan and let the fish marinate for at least 1/2 hour.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Mix oil and flour in cast-iron skillet; cook on low for 15 to 20 minutes.
It's ready when it's medium brown and has a tasty aroma.
Add onions, green pepper and garlic.
Add water; cook until onions are tender.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, hot pepper sauce and pepper.
Lay shrimp over top and cover tightly; cook 5 to 8 minutes until shrimp are starting to turn pink.
Stir in salt, ham and rice.
Cover and heat until ham is heated through. Serve with tossed salad and French bread.
tags: freshly cooked long grain white rice

title: pizza on a bun
directions: Spread pizza sauce on bun and sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese is melted or microwave 3 to 4 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: potato pie(alma henderson's)
directions: Put potatoes into blender until smooth.
Beat eggs separately; save whites for meringue.
Combine all other ingredients and bake in prepared pie crust at 400° first.
Turn down to 325°.
Do not overcook.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients. Cook over medium heat until clear.
Remove from heat, add jello.
Cool, then add strawberries and pour into two baked pie shells.
Chill.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put bread crumbs in a Pyrex dish.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together well.
Place Pyrex dish in pan of hot water about 1 inch deep.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: granny's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in order listed.
Cut in Crisco.
Stir in butter, milk and yeast water.
Knead lightly, then roll out and cut.
Bake 20 minutes in preheated 400° oven.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, eggs, breadcrumbs, cheese, milk, oregano and garlic powder together.
Roll into balls.
Brown in skillet.

title: angel biscuits or rolls
directions: Mix
all
together
just like biscuits.
Roll out dough and cut
out
biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet and let rise 30 minutes.
Put a little butter on top and bake at 350° to 400°. These will keep 3 to 4 days in the refrigerator.

title: fat-free rice krispies treats
directions: Heat honey in large saucepan until thin.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix in milk, flour and sugar.
Pour fruit or berries on top.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: stollen-hot cross buns
directions: Mix sugar and yeast (dissolved in warm water) in large bowl; stir until blended.
Mix egg, milk, shortening, salt and extract into yeast.
Sift spices and flour and blend in.
Work fruit into dough.
Cover; let rise until double.
Punch down, knead and form into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° until brown on top.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together with mixer.
Mix Cool Whip or Dream Whip with sugar and cream cheese mixture.
Put into graham cracker crumbs pie crust shells.
Top with pie filling. Makes 2 pies.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In skillet melt margarine; stir in flour, salt, cocoa, sugar, vanilla and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken when it reaches gravy stage.
Serve over biscuits cut in halves.
Serve hot.

title: housecleaning special
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese, to top the casserole.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coffee ice cream soda
directions: Make syrup ahead, refrigerated it will keep indefinitely.
Mix sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in instant coffee and vanilla extract.

title: instant fruit salad
directions: Mix instant pie mix with pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Add pineapple, mandarin oranges and bananas.
Keep refrigerated. Serves 6.

title: simmered holiday apples
directions: Lightly spray nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Pour in apple juice.
Add sugar and mix until sugar dissolves.
Simmer over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in batter, flavor mix, cinnamon and nutmeg and mix about 1 minute.
Add apples and simmer 10 to 12 minutes until apples are soft.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese royale
directions: Place bread cubes in 6-cup casserole (13 x 9). Add cheese cubes and mix.
Beat eggs; add to milk. Add salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and cheese cubes.
Let stand at least 1 hour or overnight. Stick triangles of buttered bread slices around top to form a crown.

title: sweet and sour onions
directions: Slice the onions and arrange in a 1-quart baking dish.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour over the onions.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: candied orange peel
directions: Advance preparation:
Cut peel of each orange in sixths; loosen from pulp.
Remove most of white membrane from peel.
Add peel and 1 tablespoon salt to 4 cups water.
Place a plate over top to keep peel under water.
Let stand overnight.
Drain; wash.
Place peel in saucepan.
Cover with cold water.
Heat to boiling; drain. Repeat boiling and draining 3 times.
With kitchen shears, cut peel in strips.
Combine peel, 2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook slowly until peel is translucent. Drain; roll in additional sugar.
Dry on rack overnight.
Makes 2 cups.

title: crab moire
directions: Saute seasonings in butter.
Add crabmeat.
Coat eggplant with breadcrumbs and toss with crab mixture.
Beat eggs, add sour cream.
Add to crab mixture.
Season and pour into casserole.
Top with buttered breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees about 45 minutes.

title: veal sauce
directions: Heat
oil in saucepan.
Saute garlic, veal and parsley. Brown lightly.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer
for 30 minutes.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and serve with sauce.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then the rest.
Start out on high, then lower the burner.
Stir it constantly, until it gets real thick, then pour into a baked regular pie shell (not a deep dish). Add meringue.

title: spinach cottage cheese souffle salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; cool.
Add the next two ingredients and blend well with rotary beater.
Pour into refrigerator tray and quick chill in freezer for 15 to 20 minutes until firm one inch from edge, but soft in the center.
Put into bowl and beat until fluffy.
Fold in celery, spinach, onion and cottage cheese.
Pour into a 1-quart mold or individual molds. Chill in refrigerator.
Unmold; garnish with radish roses, spinach leaves and parsley.

title: caribbean rum custard
directions: Scald first 3 ingredients and cool to lukewarm.
Whip other ingredients together until thick and lemony in color.
Add warm cream mixture.
Pour into ramekins.
Cover each with foil.
Place in baking pans.
Fill baking pans halfway with water.
Bake at 325° until custards test done, about 25 minutes.
Serves 8.
Great with Expresso.

title: tuna walnut fettuccine
directions: Prepare noodles.
During last 2 minutes of cooking noodles, stir in frozen peas.
Drain.

title: hungry jack beef
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain.
Add all other ingredients (except cheese and biscuits).
Cook until simmering.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until biscuits are done.
Put on cheese; bake until cheese is melted.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut up the pork chops into bite size pieces, removing large pieces of fat.
Brown the pork chops and onion in a skillet.
Cut the carrots into bite size pieces; cut the green pepper into strips.
Add the carrots, green pepper and water to the skillet. Cover and simmer for
30 minutes.
Drain the pineapple and save the juice.
Mix the cornstarch, brown sugar and salt in a bowl. Mix together the pineapple juice, lemon juice and soy sauce and add it gradually to the cornstarch mixture.
Gradually add this mixture to the meat mixture in the skillet, stirring constantly. Continue cooking about 5 minutes until the sauce is smooth.
Add the pineapple chunks and heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Take all ingredients, throw in large bowl.
Squish together with bare hands until thoroughly mixed.
If dry, add a little milk. Preheat oven at 350°.
Mold into large loaf pan or shape onto 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Cover with foil and cook 1 hour.
Remove foil and cook until light brown, approximately 1/2 hour.
Do not overbake.

title: snow ghost pie or pudding
directions: If you scald 2 1/2 cups of the milk it takes less time.

title: grandma's lemon cake with sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, salt, flour and baking powder. Mix well. Beat in milk and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: heavenly blueberry pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add sugar.
Crumble Ritz crackers.
Fold into egg white mixture, then add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into a heavily greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes a thick crust.
When cool, spread pie filling in crust and top with Cool Whip.
You may use any pie filling to suit your taste (peach, apple, cherry, etc.).

title: steak soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add other ingredients; simmer on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and pecan salad
directions: Combine chicken, eggs, pecans and celery.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, onion salt and pepper.
Pour over top of chicken mixture and toss.
Chill about 1 hour.
Garnish with tomatoes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add to eggs and beat.
Add butter, Pet milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 1/2 minutes with the mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: super bowl casserole
directions: Saute meat and onions; drain off excess grease.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Combine soups, sauce and chilies and add to meat.
Tear tortillas into small pieces and line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish that has been lightly greased (use Pam spray).
Pour some of meat mixture over tortillas and continue to layer tortillas and meat mixture, ending with tortillas.
Top with grated cheese and bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well and cook 2 minutes.
Put in peanut butter while still boiling.
Take off stove and put in oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper.

title: pastor's orange cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix shortening, sugar, and eggs. Stir in orange juice and rind.
Blend dry ingredients, stir in. Drop by rounded teaspoons on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chipped creamed dried beef
directions: Mix dried beef, flour and milk.
Stir until flour blends with milk.
Simmer over low heat until mixture thickens; add butter. Stir constantly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in small amount of water.
Save broth.
Remove from bone.
Layer chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan; pepper.
Add cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, milk or water and Pepperidge Farm herb seasoning.
Sprinkle on top.
Pour chicken broth on top, using own judgement as to how moist.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
I uncover mine about the last 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat the egg yolks.
Stir in the sweetened condensed milk, water and vanilla.
Fold in the crushed cookies and the whipped cream.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or any similar 2-quart container.
Cover and freeze for 6 hours.
Serve.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix soup in chicken broth and bring to a boil. Take chicken off the bones and place in a bowl. Make biscuits and drop into soup broth. Pour the meat in. Cook until done.

title: molly's tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Place 1/2 bag Tater Tots in bottom of greased pan.
Mix beef mixture, soup, Cheez Whiz and sour cream.	Place this mixture on top of hash browns.
Cover mixture with remaining Tater Tots.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine pecans, 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; stir well and set aside.
Combine shortening and 1 cup sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla; stir in sour cream. Combine remaining dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and stir just enough to blend.
Sprinkle half of reserved cinnamon mixture into bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Spoon half of butter into pan.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon mixture over batter; spoon remaining batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool cake for 5 minutes in pan on wire rack.
Loosen edges of cake, if necessary.
Invert cake on serving plate; serve warm or cold.
Yields one 10-inch coffee cake.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Mix in order and bake in a hot oven (400°) for 20 to 25 minutes for 6 large or 12 small muffins.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Bake in loaf pans (greased and floured) for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.

title: teriyaki chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook chicken in pan with 1 tablespoon oil or butter for 3 minutes, browning on all sides.
In separate pan, mix broccoli, pea pods, carrots, onions, bean sprouts and soy sauce until brownish.
Mix vegetables and chicken together in a wok or bigger pan.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Then add teriyaki sauce, sugar and 1/2 cup water; cook 3 to 4 more minutes.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well, about 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Sprinkle with nuts (optional).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Make icing while baking by combining powdered sugar, oleo, 1/3 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Take cake from oven and puncture all over with a fork.
Pour icing all over. Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Invert on plate, then back on plate you want to use.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together well and chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Dissolve soda in milk and add alternately with flour mixture.
Add vanilla, then bananas and nuts and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes clean from center.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in a large bowl in the microwave for 2 minutes.
Coat sandwiches with almond bark.
Cool on wax paper. Keep chilled.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Shape the first 5 ingredients into small balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Combine soup and water; add to meat balls.
Cook 15 minutes.
Good served over rice.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with your favorite frosting.

title: old fashion lemon bars
directions: Cream together butter, confectioners sugar and flour. Spread evenly on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Beat eggs and mix with salt, sugar, lemon juice, lemon rind, flour and baking powder. Pour mixture over cooked pastry. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Cool for 15 minutes and cut into oblong finger-shaped. Keep lemon bars in fridge.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in slices about 3/8 inch thick.
Dip into flour seasoned with salt and paprika.
Saute onions until yellow. Remove onions with slotted spoon.
Leave fat in pan.
Brown meat slices; remove from pan.
Put remaining seasoned flour into pan; stir.
When flour and fat are mixed thoroughly, add boiling water, stir until gravy is made.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce; if too thick, add more water, bring to a boil.
Strain, pour over meat and onions that have been put into casserole.
Bake tightly covered in 325° oven until meat is tender.

title: potato patties
directions: Add flour to mixture to make a thicker consistency than pancake batter.
Mix all ingredients together and fry in cooking oil until brown.

title: corn and pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container until well blended. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve well chilled.

title: mama's apple cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients and beat well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Using back of spoon, dipped in flour, spread batter evenly in pan.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at once.
Beat on low speed for 4 minutes; pour into pans or pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes if 9-inch pans; 30 to 40 minutes if a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
This is a moist dark chocolate cake; may be frosted or left unfrosted.

title: honey 'n' fruit chicken salad
directions: In large bowl stir together sour cream, cinnamon and honey. Stir in all remaining ingredients until well coated.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour to chill.
Yields 8 servings; 210 calories per serving, 7 g fat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add cream of mushroom soup to cooked broccoli.
Mix; add cooked rice.
Mix; add Cheez Whiz and mix.
Put into a casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: microwave nachos-el-more-o
directions: Spread the chips on a plate that is safe for a microwave oven. Sprinkle the grated cheese over the chips.
Put the plate of chips in the microwave oven for 30 to 45 seconds.
When the microwave oven stops, take out the plate of chips.
Spread the taco sauce over the chips and melted cheese.
Eat and enjoy the Nachos-El-More-O.

title: sugarless pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine and beat together until creamed the honey, oil, eggs and pumpkin. Sift together the whole-wheat flour, baking powder, baking soda, ground cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture until blended. Fold in parboiled raisins. Pour mixture into muffin cups or greased muffin tins (unless using greaseless tins). If you have dark tins, watch time of baking to avoid burning bottoms. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes and remove to baking racks for cooling. Makes 1 dozen.

title: honey poppy seed dressing
directions: Prepare salad oil, honey, vinegar, poppy seed and mustard in a small jar and shake well.
Wash and clean lettuce and berries. Slice onion and separate into rings.
Layer berries, onions and lettuce.
(Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.)
Pour dressing over before serving.
Makes a beautiful and delicious dish.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar and shortening together well. Add eggs, soda and bananas.
Stir in flour.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 50 to 60 minutes.
To test if done, press on center.
If it springs back, it is done.

title: salmon patties
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon; flake salmon in liquid. Add crumbs, onion, egg and milk; mix well.
Shape into balls. Melt butter over low heat in a skillet.
Add salmon balls.
Cook about 5 minutes on each side.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Combine the first eight ingredients.
Blend well.
Chocolate chips may be sprinkled on top.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage; put aside.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and cut up in little pieces.
Remove pan from heat; add vinegar and sugar to bacon grease.
Stir until dissolved.
Add bacon to mixture.
Put back on stove on low heat.
When ready to serve, pour mixture over cabbage.

title: lemonade tea
directions: Prepare lemonade as directed on can.
Stir in tea.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with mint.

title: celery casserole
directions: Wash, string and slice celery about 1/4-inch.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and pour into dish.
Heat soup and pour over celery.
Add slices of water chestnuts.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Sprinkle over celery mixture and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: teriyaki sauce(marinade)
directions: Mix and marinate meat 5 hours or more. Turn often. Save what is left over.
Freeze to use later.
If you mix in a leakproof Ziploc bag, no dish to wash.
Good on beef, pork or chicken. Grill as usual.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat in olive oil; add onion and cook over medium heat until onion is tender.
Stir in seasonings, tomatoes, soup and rice.
Add half of olive slices; simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with cheese strips and remaining olive slices.
Bake until heated through and cheese is melted.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Place Marshmallow Creme and kisses in large bowl; set aside. Combine sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil; cook for 8 minutes.
Pour over Marshmallow Creme and kisses, stirring until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Yields about 12 dozen.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Prepare broccoli as label directs; drain.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Brown meat.
Pour off all grease.
(You may want to rinse meat off.)
In a saucepan pour low-fat beef gravy.
If you want it real meaty tasting add a beef bouillon cube with a little water; add 1 container of fat-free sour cream and add some milk if too thick. Stir while heating and add meat to gravy mix.
(I sometimes add a little cooking wine for a different flavor.)
Serve over egg-free noodles.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips in a double boiler.
Add peanuts.
Drop clusters onto waxed paper.

title: welch cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients all together, then add shortening (part butter).
Work well into dry items, then add currants.
Beat eggs and add milk with vanilla.
Roll out and cut and fry on ungreased griddle or electric frying pan.
Cooks very fast.
Sometimes extra flour is needed.

title: vegetarian burritos
directions: Heat tortillas according to package. Heat olive oil in large skillet. Add carrots, onion and garlic; cook, stirring constantly 2 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce and next 7 ingredients; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Spoon about 1/2 cup vegetable mixture down centers of warm tortillas; sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese. Fold opposite sides over filling, securing with a wooden pick if necessary. Serve immediately with salsa and guacamole.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Brown pork in oil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove pork and saute vegetables.
Remove. Blend jam, juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Stir a little sauce with cornstarch and ginger.
Add to skillet and cook until mixture thickens.
Stir in pork, pineapple and vegetables.
May be served with rice.
Serves 4.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving the juice; place beets in glass jar. Boil vinegar and beet juice; add sugar, cloves and bay leaf and heat to boiling.
Pour all ingredients over beets.
Cover the jar and refrigerate.
Serve beets very cold.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Just before removing from oven, top with miniature marshmallows and brown.

title: chicken salad cream puff ring
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil. Add flour and salt.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms ball.
Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of batter onto ungreased cookie sheet to form a 10-inch ring.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from cookie sheet immediately. Cool.

title: chicken breasts with andouille sauce
directions: Clean and trim breasts and dredge in flour, shaking off excess.
Heat oil and cook chicken quickly on both sides.
Remove and keep warm. Saute the onion, garlic, bell pepper and andouille. Cook over low heat and add the tomatoes, vermouth, bay leaf and thyme.
Let simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes. Add the chicken and let it heat thoroughly. Serve. Good with rice.

title: mother's burnt sugar pie
directions: Combine egg yolks and milk.
Mix flour with 1/3 cup sugar and add to egg mixture a little at a time.
Set aside.
Burn the cup of sugar (in an iron skillet if possible) to a very dark brown, but do not scorch.
When sugar is ready, add egg mixture and cook until thick.
Cool a little, then add butter and vanilla.
Have crust cooked and cooled ahead of time.
Top with egg whites.

title: ms. green's tex-mex rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and beef base.
Stir until beef base is dissolved.
Add rice.
Simmer, stirring occasionally until flavors are blended.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy lemonade pie
directions: Just mix all ingredients together.
Put in pie crust; chill for about an hour.
Enjoy!

title: okra surprise
directions: Thoroughly rinse sliced okra under running water; drain well. Combine okra and remaining ingredients in a large skillet.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread bean mixture in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed. Serve with corn chips.
Yield:
8 cups.

title: peanutty chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sour cream and eggs until smooth. Add cake mix; mix together until smooth. Using large scoop, place 12 scoops of batter into bottom of fluted pan; spread evenly. Arrange peanut butter cups in a circular pattern over batter. Top with remaining batter and spread evenly. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tester inserted near center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes on cooling rack. Loosen cake from sides of pan. Carefully invert onto round platter.

title: sugar tea cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream.
Add egg and mix.
Sift soda and flour and mix.
Flatten out small ball of dough on floured board and roll thin.
Cut in desired shapes.
Bake until golden brown in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate chunk pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet.
Cream the butter and shortening with the sugar and salt until light and well blended.
Stir in the vanilla and egg.
Stir in the flour and baking soda and mix well.

Fold in the nuts and chocolate chunks. Form into generous tablespoons of batter and drop onto the baking sheet, pressing down slightly on the dough, about 2 inches apart. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until lightly golden in color and browned at the edges.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry hamburg but do not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, onion, garlic and parsley.
Cook.
Cook noodles dente.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheeses, ending with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Let stand before cutting.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook all ingredients except nuts until it forms a firm ball; let it cool for 15 minutes.
Add nuts.
Use large pan.

title: water rising twists
directions: Combine shortening, 3 tablespoons sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Stir to melt shortening, then when lukewarm, crumble in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add half the flour and beat until smooth.
Cover and let rest for about 15 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add remaining flour and mix thoroughly.
Place in a piece of cheesecloth.
Bring corners of cloth together and submerge ball of dough in bowl of ice water.
Let stand until dough rises to top of water.
Remove from water.
(Dough will be soft and moist.)
Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Divide dough into small pieces with a tablespoon. Roll each piece lightly in sugar, cinnamon and nut mixture and stretch to about an 8-inch length.
Twist to desired shape (crescent) and place on greased baking sheet.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: impossible meat pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion with taco seasoning or chili powder in skillet.
Mix mild taco sauce, Bisquick, eggs and milk.
Pour over top of meat in baking pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.
After baked, top with cheese.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Butter a baking dish.
Place in it alternate layers of the vegetables, starting and ending with the green beans.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and paprika.
Dot with butter.
Cover the dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until the beans are tender. Goes great with pork chops.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain berries and pineapple.
Measure liquid and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Stir in blueberries and pineapple. Pour in 2-quart mold
and refrigerate until firm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper, soup and cheese; mix well.
Spoon into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with corn flake crumbs; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in just enough water to cover.
While potatoes are cooking, fry out sausage and drain, then crumble; add to potatoes.
When potatoes are almost done, add remaining ingredients, "except noodles."
Cook 30 minutes.
Cut off heat. Add noodles and let set until noodles are done, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable cornucopia salad
directions: Tear greens into bite-size pieces; combine greens and vegetables in a large salad bowl.
Add rest of the ingredients; toss and serve with favorite dressing.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook beans according to basic directions.
Saute onions and garlic in peanut oil until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cook 10 minutes; add the beans with the bean broth, corn, olives and hot pepper sauce.
Cook until heated through.
Adjust seasonings.

Skim and reserve 1 cup of the thinner top of the bean mixture for sauce to pass at the table. Line an oiled 3 1/2 or 4 quart casserole dish with tortillas. Spoon over them a thick layer (about 1 inch) of bean mixture and sprinkle a few scallions on the beans.
Scatter some cheese evenly over top.
Reserve 1 cup of the cheese and some scallions for use later.
Continue making layers of tortillas, beans, scallions and cheese, ending with the bean mixture until the dish is nearly full.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until casserole is bubbling and heated through.

title: georgia powell's spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach until able to squeeze water out of it.
Place in a bowl.
Add all ingredients.
Be sure to chop chestnuts into small pieces.
Stir until well blended.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers, Wheat Thins, etc.

title: banana pudding for ben
directions: Heat in saucepan and stir constantly until it boils.
Turn off heat.
Keep stirring (a wire whip works best).
Add teaspoon vanilla and teaspoon nutmeg.
(If too thick, add a little water and keep stirring.)
Layer banana slices and vanilla wafers and pudding.
Crumble wafers on top!

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows. Add all other ingredients. Pack well into a well-greased pan and let sit for 24 hours. Can be frozen and keeps well.

title: microwave oriental ham
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in butter on Medium 5 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients; cover.
Cook on High 10 minutes. Toss and serve.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cook raspberries, water, sugar and cornstarch until thick. Cool.
Combine margarine, oatmeal, flour, nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and soda.
Reserve 2 cups of flour-oatmeal mixture.
Pat down remainder in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cooled fruit on top. Cover with reserved 2 cups of mixture.
Pat down.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well flour, sugar and cocoa together.
Stir in 2 cups milk and heat on low heat.
When warm, beat the remaining 1/2 cup of milk with the egg yolks.
Pour into warm mixture slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add margarine.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend the flour, sugar, oil and eggs.
Add apples, nuts, coconut, raisins, soda, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in quiche pan or pie pan.
Make a well in the middle and pour in milk and stick of oleo.
Do not stir.
Put in microwave 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until oleo melts.
Remove and stir.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour in greased pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: beets royale
directions: Heat juice.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Add vinegar, salt, pineapple chunks, beets and sugar (only if pineapple was in its own juice).
Heat thoroughly.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Pour half of Dream Whip mixture over pecans.
Pour cherry pie filling over whipped cream.
Pour the rest of Dream Whip on top.
Chill overnight.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top or pecans.

title: pizza hot dish casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix flour with 1/4 cup tomato juice (reserved from drained tomatoes).
Stir oil, flour and juice mixture into meat.
Add tomatoes, onion and spices.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Top with corn flakes or potato chips.
Dot with butter and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk, egg yolks and margarine.
Cook on simmer until soft and thick.
Remove and cool about 5 minutes and stir.
Add pecans, coconut and vanilla.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box for sheet cake. While cake is still hot, poke holes in it with a wooden spoon handle.
Pour the can of sweetened condensed milk over cake and let cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Make pudding. Mix all ingredients together. Chill and eat with dinner or dessert.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Grease and flour large tube pan or two loaf pans; preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together in large bowl the sugar, shortening, egg and pinto beans until thoroughly blended.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices; add gradually to bean mixture, beating well.
Fold in chopped apples, raisins and black walnuts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Heat until hot.
Serve with crackers.

title: fish stuffed with crab
directions: Thaw frozen fish; cut fish in half lengthwise.
Remove bones. Cut garlic; rub cut edge of garlic over all surfaces of the fish. Sprinkle with lime juice, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.
Place one half of the fish in a well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan skin side down.

title: queen elizabeth ii cake
directions: Pour water over dates and soda.
Let stand while mixing remaining ingredients.
Add to date mixture and bake in 9 x 12-inch pan 30 minutes in moderate oven, or until done.

title: finnish bread cookies
directions: Mix butter, 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Take a little at a time and roll into small bread sticks.
Cut into about 1-inch strips. Dip in sweet cream and then press into sugar and almonds.
Bake until brown at 300°.

title: pineapple fluff pie
directions: In a bowl, combine the pineapple and pudding mix until thickened; fold in the whipped topping.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate until serving.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: barbecue lima beans
directions: Drain.
Mix lima beans and barbecue sauce together in baking dish.
Bake for about 35 minutes.
Simple and great.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix well.
Boil 15 minutes.
Pour over 3 beaten egg whites, beating all the time.
Add nuts.
Beat until it loses its gloss.

title: buns
directions: Put yeast, 2 teaspoons sugar and 1/2 cup warm water in a small bowl; mix and let raise for a few minutes.
Put 1 1/2 cups sugar, 3 teaspoons salt and the oil in a large bowl.
Add the yeast mixture.
Add 5 cups warm water.
Slowly add flour as you mix. Knead about 5 minutes.
Put in large pan to raise for 2 hours. Punch down; let raise for 2 more hours.
Make out into buns on cookie sheet.
Let raise for 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Melt over steam and beat into mayonnaise.
Add sugar to cream and whip, then combine with mayonnaise.
Stir in fruit.
Pour in trays and freeze.
Serve on lettuce.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat eggs at high speed until thick.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar and beat 5 additional minutes. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients.
Gradually stir in pumpkin mixture. Spread batter evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and press in batter.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: "hot cocoa" cake(this is a very rich, but very easy cake.)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil.
Mix together (sifting is a good idea) the flour and sugar.
Add dry ingredients to saucepan (which you have cooled slightly).
Mix well and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes.
Leave in pan.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Place in layers in pan.
Place slices of oleo on top

title: swiss venison steak
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil.
Put into deep roaster. Saute onion and pepper until soft. Add to roaster.
Add soup (1 for 1 pound or 2 for 2 pound) to pan with 1 cup water. Bring to a boil and add to roaster.
Bake in oven 2 to 3 hours. Can also be cooked in crock-pot.
Tastes better if cooked the day before serving.

title: chocolate confetti
directions: Melt butter with peanut butter in a large saucepan.
Stir in chips until melted.
Cool so that you can hold your hand on the bottom of the pan.
Add marshmallows and stir until all are coated.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Cut veal into 6 servings. Pound meat with meat mallet to flatten a little. Mix flour, salt and pepper together. Coat veal steaks with flour mixture. Brown steaks in shortening. Add sherry and simmer for 1 hour or place in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove and finely chop mushroom stems.
Place mushroom caps, right side up, on foil-lined broiler pan.
Brush tops of caps with 1 tablespoon oil.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: cheeseburger and fries casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Stir in soups.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange french fries on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50-55 minutes.

title: corn slaw
directions: Combine corn, onion, pepper and carrots.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Combine vegetables and dressing.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles with 3/4 teaspoon salt until tender.
Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining 7 ingredients.
Simmer over low to medium heat until sauce becomes thick, approximately 30 minutes. Grease a casserole dish.
Layer noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Ricotta cheese.
Make all layers in the same order.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: 100 hole cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer until smooth.
Pour into a tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: italian chicken
directions: Combine flour and garlic powder and toss with chicken to coat.
In large pan, heat oil over medium high heat.
Add chicken and cook 3-4 minutes each side until brown and cooked.
Combine next 3 ingredients and add to pan.	Simmer 5 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until cheese melts.	Serve over noodles.

title: sausage snacks
directions: Cut each crescent roll in half; roll up sausage.
Bake as per instructions for rolls on package.

title: butter cookie christmas cut-outs
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add confectioners sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla; beat well. Stir together the dry ingredients; blend into cream mixture. Chill dough about an hour.
Roll on well-floured pastry board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with floured cookie cutter.
Bake on an unbuttered cookie sheet approximately 5 minutes at 400°.
Yield: 6 dozen cookies (depends on the cutter).

title: pecan tarts crust
directions: Mix together and put in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: buterhorns
directions: Mix together sour cream & egg yolk.
Cut butter into flour as you would for a pie crust.
Add sour cream & egg yolk to mixture. Mix well and shape into a ball.
Wrap well and chill overnight. Divide into 3 parts and roll each into a circle and cut into pie shaped wedges (12).
Put 1 tsp. of filling on the wide end of the roll up.
Bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet at 375° for 25-30 minutes until just lightly browned.
Chill & dust with powdered sugar.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except powdered sugar.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cornflake crunchies
directions: Mix sugar and Karo in a boiler and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour over cornflakes. Make sure all flakes are covered.
Pinch or drop into small balls and cool on wax paper.
Put into storage container before hardening a lot.

title: sweet chocolate pie
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, margarine and nuts.
Press onto bottom and sides of pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool. Combine marshmallows, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Cool.
Blend in vanilla.

title: peach pie
directions: In large mixing bowl combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in La Creme and peaches.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.

title: spiced apple and raisin sauce
directions: In medium skillet over medium heat, cook apple in margarine until tender.
Stir in brown sugar, raisins and cloves.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well.
Stir into apple mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens stirring constantly.
Serve warm over turkey.

title: broccoli cornbread(great with chili or potato soup.)
directions: Pre-heat oven 375 degrees

title: my mom's meat loaf
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Form into a loaf and place in a large baking pan.
The bottom of an oven broiler works well. Place in an oven at 350 degrees and begin cooking uncovered for 30 minutes. Dissolve the bouillon cube in 1 C. water.
Drain any grease from pan.
Pour beef broth over meat loaf and return to oven for another 30 minutes.
Make up gravy packages according to directions on pack.
Pour over meat loaf.
Continue cooking another 30 - 50 minutes until done.
Internal temperature of 155 degrees.
Baste with gravy several times while cooking.

title: clam chowder
directions: Strain clams.
Save liquid.
Chop clams.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of bacon fat until brown.
Simmer potatoes in water until tender.
Add reserved clam liquid, bacon, onion, salt and pepper to taste; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add milk; bring to a boil. Add clams and barely heat through.
Taste and correct seasoning. Add butter and thyme to each serving.
Cook clams first.
Add thyme.
Put parsley on for decoration.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Put sweetened condensed milk into mixing bowl. Gradually add lemon juice to milk. Then add egg yolks and stir until well blended and thickened. Pour filling into pie shell. Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until stiff enough to hold peak. Add 1 tablespoon sugar at a time, beating until stiff and glossy. Pile lightly onto pie filling. Bake at 325° until lightly browned. Be careful not to burn. Keep in fridge.

title: baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breast halves in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine tomatoes and remaining ingredients, stirring until well mixed.
Spoon over chicken in dish.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: quick rumtopf
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Ladle into clean, sterilized jars.
Store in a cool place.
Let age 1 month before serving. Makes about 3 pints. Can be served over ice cream or pound cake.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt or angel food cake pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove.
Ice with soft icing.
Glaze while still warm.

title: vienna boiled beef(weiner tafelspitz)
directions: Heat 2 quarts water with salt.
Add beef; bring to a boil. Skim foam from surface until clear.
Partially cover pot; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Cut leeks in 2-inch pieces, then cut in half lengthwise.
Add leeks, onion, carrots and celery to beef.
Cook until beef and vegetables are tender.
Cut beef into 1/2-inch slices.
Cut gherkins lengthwise in thin slices, leaving 1 end uncut.
Spread out slices like a fan; garnish beef with gherkins. Serve vegetables in a separate dish with 4 tablespoons cooking liquid spooned over the top.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with Swedish mayonnaise.

title: green stuff
directions: Mix together well.
Allow to stand at least 4 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: mom's pimento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients using a potato masher.
Mash until spread is creamy.

title: great guacamole
directions: Take the skin off of the avocado, then remove the pit.
Chop the avocado into small pieces.
Place avocado and all other ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Blend all ingredients.
Add a dash of Tabasco sauce or other hot sauce, if desired.
Store with the avocado pit resting in bowl in order to not turn brown. Serve as soon as possible with tortilla chips for dipping.
Our family especially likes Blue corn chips.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix and drop on cookie sheet.
Press nut on each.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, oil and cream of tartar.
Cook on low heat and add food coloring and water to make desired color.
Add to mixture.
Cook until like mashed potatoes.
Store in plastic bag in refrigerator.

title: mrs. claus' fudge(makes about 5 pounds)
directions: Mix butter, milk and sugar in heavy saucepan.
Let reach bubbly boil.
Turn burner down to medium.
Cook 8 or 9 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Add vanilla, nuts and marshmallows.
Pour in an 18 x 12-inch pan.
Let stand for a while (overnight if possible) before cutting.
Freezes well.
Put waxed paper between layers.

title: cheeseburger cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease spring-form pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Mix ground beef, onion and all remaining ingredients, except cheese and sesame seed. Spread half of batter in pan.
Lay cheese slices on batter.
Cover with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms clean and remove stems.
Melt butter and add garlic salt.
Saute mushrooms for 1 minute on each side.
Turn upside down on brown paper.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake until set.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water in a Dutch oven.
Stir in orange juice and next three ingredients.
Pour mixture into a large plastic container.
Then freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.
Place in a punch bowl and break into chunks.
Add lemon-lime soda.
Stir until slushy.
Yields about 6 quarts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries, oranges, apples and orange rind.
Add the sugar.
Mix well.
Dissolve the Jell-O in the hot water.
Add the cold pineapple juice.
Chill and add the cranberry mixture, pineapple, nuts and grapes.
Put in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and stir in cranberries.
Spoon batter into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix together beans and green pepper.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill overnight.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix eggs and flour.
Add water, salt and coloring.
Knead well.
Divide into 6 balls; chill slightly.
Roll dough as thin as a shammy.
Cut and dry well before storing.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Place warm water
in
bowl.
Add dry milk and mix well. Add sugar and mix until smooth.
After mixing, allow to set in refrigerator for a	while
to
chill.
This allows the milk to thicken.
If it
doesn't
seem
thick
enough, 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons cornstarch may be added.

title: praline grahams
directions: Separate each graham cracker into sections.
Arrange on a cookie sheet with edges touching.
Melt butter in a saucepan; stir in sugar and pecans.
Bring to a boil; cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spread mixture evenly over graham crackers.
Bake at 300°
for 12 minutes.
Cut apart and remove from pan,
and let cool on wax paper.
Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: tommy's cheese and eggs
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Turn burner off.
Break eggs one at a time in skillet.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cut up cheese in skillet.
Scramble eggs and cheese together.
Turn burner on low.
Scramble eggs until done.

title: tofu salad
directions: Combine in small pot and bring to fast boil.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil until thickened the sugar, 7-Up and cornstarch.
Stir in strawberry jello.
Put strawberries in cooled pie shell and pour mixture over them.
Top with cream.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate sharp cheese; mix with remaining ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill.
Garnish with additional mandarin oranges sections if desired.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups or 6 servings.

title: surprisin' carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round pans.
In bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl, mix on medium the next 4 ingredients until well blended.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until well mixed.
With spoon stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour in pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans.
Fill and frost with whipped cream.

title: dirt cake
directions: Stir milk into pudding mix and set aside.
Soften cream cheese (one minute in microwave) and mix with Cool Whip.
Stir into pudding mixture, it can be a little lumpy.
Alternate layers of crushed Oreos with filling in a large flowerpot, ending with Oreos on top.
Chill until ready to serve.
Insert artificial flowers in straws and poke into mixture, creating a nice looking arrangement.

title: crab puffs
directions: Toast bread rounds on one side.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in mayo, crab and Cheddar cheese.
Spread mixture on untoasted side of round.
Broil until bubbly and serve.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart bowl (High for 30 to 45 seconds). Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually whisk in milk until smooth.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring twice, until boiling and slightly thickened.

title: better than sex(easier too!!)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350°.
Stir after first 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Press flat on ungreased cookie sheet.
(May be frozen to bake later.) Cook 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: crustless cheese cake
directions: Blend Ricotta and cream cheese at medium speed using electric mixer.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Stir in the juice of 1/2 lemon, vanilla, cornstarch, flour and the melted butter. Blend it all until smooth; add the sour cream and mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch greased spring-form pan.
Start oven after cake is put into oven.
The oven must be cold.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° and do not open oven door.
Let the cake remain in the oven for 2 hours after heat is turned off.
Place cake in pan on rack and let it get completely cold before removing.
Top it with your favorite fruit pie filling.

title: hot cinnamon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8-inch square pan.
In a large bowl combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Add milk and beat well.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: friendship candy
directions: Brown pecans until you smell them in the 1/2 teaspoon butter. Mix sugar and cheese with fork.
Add pecans and drop on wax paper. Store in a cool place.

title: rum coffee strips(easy refrigerator cookies)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream the butter and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and flavoring; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients; blend.
Shape into 2 flat rectangles and chill overnight after wrapping in wax paper.

title: rice pilaf 2
directions: Saute rice, onion and celery with oleo until golden brown on low heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Soak raisins in 3 eggs, beaten with vanilla, for at least an hour (the longer, the better).
Cream sugars with margarine.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients together. Batter will be stiff.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.
Cool; store in airtight container.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Boil for 1 minute.
Let cool and pour over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, sugars and vanilla in large mixer bowl until creamy. Beat in eggs. Beat in flour. Stir in 3/4 cup of chocolate morsels. Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with remaining morsels. Let stand 3 to 5 minutes. Spread to cover. Cool in pan before cutting.

title: crawfish etouffee #2
directions: Saute all vegetables in butter until tender; add 2 tablespoons flour.
Stir well.
Then add 1 cup tomato sauce; stir well.
Add 2 quarts of water.
Cook until thickened under low flame.
Add 2 pounds precooked crawfish tails and season to taste with Tony's Creole seasoning.
Serve with rice.

title: easy taco pie
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with assorted chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: bass soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until tender.
Let water get sort of cooked out of pan.
Add tomatoes and cook until tender.
Add pinch of soda and stir.
Add milk and macaroni.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: golden chicken and vegetables
directions: Cut chicken into thin narrow strips.
Combine with 1 teaspoon stir-fry sauce.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in hot wok or large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in same pan.
Add onion and garlic; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add carrots and celery; stir-fry 2 minutes.

title: chocolate-tipped butter cookies* * * * *
directions: Round Steak with Mushroom Gravy is from a sister-in-law.
She was from Michigan, but moved to Iowa in 1949.
Everything else on the menu, except the sorbet, is from that time.
The sorbet came from one of the cookbooks which I have collected through the years.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Mix together sugar, Wesson oil, vinegar and tomato soup.
Bring to a boil.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Pour mixture over drained carrots and mix.
Keeps well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Stir together the flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat sugars, butter and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Beat in sour cream alternately with dry ingredients.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes, or until wooden picks come out clean.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: cherry-mallow dessert
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler.
Add vanilla and cool. Whip the cream. Fold into cooled marshmallow mixture. Line a 9 x 9-inch pan with crushed wafers or crackers. Add marshmallow mixture.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Let stand overnight. Serves 9.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil water.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and strawberry mix and slowly add dry ingredients into boiling water so as not to become lumpy.
Boil for 3 minutes until bright red.
Let stand until cool while slicing strawberries in cooled pie shell.
Then pour cooled filling over strawberries and place in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sallie's blackened rolls
directions: Note:
Recipe may be doubled or tripled in the absence of a main dish.

title: stir-n-roll pie crust(double crust)
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Pour Wesson oil and milk together, do not
stir.
Add
all
at once to flour.
Stir until mixed. Press into smooth ball.
Cut in half; flatten slightly.
Place 1/2 between
sheets
of
waxed paper.
Dampen table top to prevent slipping.
Roll out gently to edges of paper, peel off top
paper, place
paper side up in 8 to 9-inch pie pan, peel off
paper. Ease
and
form
pastry into pan.
Trim even with rim,
add filling.
Roll
top
crust as directed and place on top.

title: fruit salad
directions: In small bowl, combine honey, lemon juice, poppy seed and grated lemon peel.
Toss cantaloupe, honeydew and pineapple chunks in honey mixture and arrange on plate with grapes.
Sprinkle with walnuts and serve chilled.

title: holiday squares
directions: Grease pan lightly.
Combine corn flake crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press down firmly with back of a spoon to form a crust.
Layer marshmallows, coconut and cherries evenly over crust.
Pour milk evenly over cherries.
Layer nuts over top, pressing lightly into mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Refrigerate before cutting.
Makes about 48 (1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: whole grain quick bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Pour milk and molasses over bran.
Add egg and shortening.
Add flour mixture and raisins.
Blend.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Cut margarine into cake mix, stir in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Arrange peach slices over crust.
Mix egg and sour cream together, dribble over peaches.
Sprinkle sugar/cinnamon over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: "miss kitty's" canned beets
directions: Mix water, vinegar and sugar.
Bring cooked beets to a boil in mixture.
Pack while hot.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Melt jello with hot water.
Add blueberries with juice.
Add pineapple with juice.
Let congeal.

title: tantalizing raspberry tarts
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Cut butter into flour mixture.
Mix egg yolk with water and lemon juice, sprinkle over flour mixture.
Mix until ball forms.
Divide dough into 12 balls. Press each ball into bottom and sides of muffin tin.
Refrigerate tart shells while making filling.

title: peanut butter pie(sugar-free)
directions: Combine crumbs with margarine and Equal.
Mix until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press firmly in bottom and sides of an 8 or 9-inch pie plate. Chill crust.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes and drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and boil mixture for 10 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars immediately.

title: favorite cajun catfish
directions: Place 1/4-inch water in broiling pan. Heat broiler. Rinse fish. Place in pan. Squeeze lemon juice over fish. Sprinkle with salt and garlic powder. Sprinkle with Cajun seafood spice until fish is completely covered. Sprinkle with small amount of olive oil. Broil 5 minutes. Turn carefully. Broil 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Check frequently - do not overcook. Serve with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: In heavy saucepan, cook onions and garlic in butter and olive oil.
When limp (not brown), add beef and cook, stirring frequently until well done.
Add wine; cover tightly and steam for 5 minutes.
Add basil, tomato paste, puree and juice.
Add green pepper, celery, black pepper to taste and nutmeg and cook for 10 minutes.
Boil lasagne in water for 15 minutes.
Put in cold water, then drain.

title: classic french toast
directions: Heat skillet or griddle to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except French bread slices.
Beat well.
Lightly grease heated skillet.
Dip bread in half and half mixture, turning to coat both sides.
Cook in skillet over medium heat for about 2 to 3 minutes on each side, or until golden brown.
If desire, sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.

title: ice cream
directions: You will need a 1 gallon ice cream freezer.

title: mexican pea casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Heat soup.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining onions and bake about 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix until peanut butter is melted.
Add oats and mix well.
Drop on sheet of wax paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: great grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add rest of dry ingredients.
Form into balls and roll in sugar.
Grease cookie sheet and put a ball at time on sheet and take the bottom of a glass and press dough flat.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. The cookies are crisp and tasty.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and cut potatoes in squares, cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Cool.
In mixing bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Fold in potatoes.
Pour into lightly greased baking dish.
Mix 1 Tbsp. margarine and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Stir ingredients (do not use a blender) thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes in a pound cake pan.

title: croutons
directions: Slice bread into 3/8-inch cubes and place in a bowl.
Add seasonings and oil.
Toss well to mix.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 300° until crisp.
Cool.
Store in a glass jar.
Costs about 1/3 of purchased croutons.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Dip chicken breasts in bread crumbs and place in a casserole dish.
Cover with Swiss cheese.
Mix milk and soup in a bowl and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple butter cookies
