directions: Mix all ingredients together. Grease cookie sheet. Roll out dough. Cut out cookie. Put in pan. Spoon on filling (apple butter). Place another cookie on top. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: white bean soup
directions: Soak
beans
overnight.
Cook
neck
bones a little, add beans, onion
and
season to taste with seasoned salt and black pepper.
Add potatoes and shredded carrots when almost done.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Melt the oleo in casserole dish. Add the onion, water chestnuts, pimento, soup and peas.
Cover with bread crumbs.
I use cracker crumbs instead.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage soup
directions: Put sausage, onion, celery and bell pepper in pot.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Add the canned ingredients.
Simmer and serve.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, egg and shortening until shortening is almost melted.
Add yeast mixture.
Add flour slowly and mix well.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Roll out and cut.
Let stand 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: grandma's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Peel, core and slice apples. Set aside. Line pie plate with 1 ready-made pie crust.

title: artichoke parmesan dip
directions: In a blender, combine cottage cheese, chives, milk, seasoned salt, basil, garlic and Tabasco sauce.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Stir in the chopped artichokes and Parmesan cheese. Transfer dip to a small serving bowl.
Cover and chill about 4 hours.
Dip will thicken as it chills.
Serve with assorted raw vegetables.
Yields about 14 (2 tablespoon) servings.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream sugars, butter and peanut butter.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir into egg mixture.
Shape into balls.
Roll in additional granulated sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately press a chocolate kiss into each cookie. Makes 7 dozen.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread.
Dice all ingredients and mix well with mayonnaise and creamy cucumber salad dressing.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix all of the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
In another bowl, whisk egg, milk, sour cream, melted butter and vanilla. Make a well in the dry ingredients, blending lightly.
Quickly fold in nuts (if desired) and chocolate morsels.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tins (or use paper baking cups) and bake at 375° until tester comes out clean, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.
Enjoy.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well and bake in 375° oven until set, about 30 minutes.

title: apple spice bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven 400°. Coat 6 cup Bundt pan with cooking spray. Stir together the flours, baking soda and spices until well combined.
In a separate bowl, beat together the egg whites, brown sugar, applesauce and oil.
Fold egg mixture into flour mixture along with fruits and nuts until well blended.
Pour into pan. Bake 30-35 minutes or till toothpick comes our clean.
Cool 5 minutes on wire rack, then carefully take out of pan and finish cooling.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Prepare fried rice according to package directions.
Add chicken and sour cream to taste.
Heat thoroughly.
Feeds 5 to 6.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and cook until blended and heated thoroughly.
Serve in a small crockpot to keep warm. Serve with crackers, tortillas, chips, or Fritos.

title: oyster cracker ranch mix
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add dressing; mix for approximately 10 minutes.
Add oyster crackers.
Let sit in hot mixture for 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 10 minutes.

title: beef and eggplant supper
directions: Cook ground beef in large skillet until browned, stirring often to crumble.
Drain off fat.
Remove meat and set aside.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Put the first three ingredients in pan and heat.
Mix until cheese melts.
Pour the cheese sauce over the noodles and other mixture and mix well.
Grease a casserole and pour the mixture in the dish.
Sprinkle the top with grated cheese and cover.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt, eggs and pickles.
Moisten with mayonnaise.
Serve on sandwiches or in lettuce cups.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: baked fruit casserole
directions: Place prunes in glass (Pyrex) casserole and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Layer remaining ingredients sprinkling with cinnamon. Bake in 325 oven for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: chicken a la suisse
directions: *Can use country ham, steamed in skillet.
Leave grease and water.
Trim fat off.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil, water, flour, spices, soda, salt and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into small loaf pans and bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.
Makes 6 to 7 small loaves.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake according to instructions on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, cut in half lengthwise.
Follow instructions on pudding box for chocolate mousse.
Refrigerate until thick, then layer.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples, being careful not to cut through blossom end. Place in shallow baking dish.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt together and spoon into centers of each apple.
Pour orange juice over apples.
Cover and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, until apples are tender.
Baste occasionally with syrup.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together; fold in eggs.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
If batter seems too sticky to roll out, add 1/2 to 1 more cup flour.
Cut cookies out thick.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Place potatoes in large stock pot, cover with water and cook until done.
Using a potato masher, mash some of the potatoes to thicken the soup.
Add carrot and celery and cook a while longer. Add butter and leek soup mix and bring back to boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste and heavy cream.
Stir well and serve.

title: grandma wright's squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: easter egg roll
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk and salt.
Mix well.
Put on low heat and stir until milk and eggs curdle; will look like sour milk. Pour into bag or cloth and tie tight to form a ball.
Let drip overnight.
Take out of bag and cloth.
Re-cover and put in refrigerator.
Slice as you would cheese.
Will keep for weeks.
If you like cheese, you will like this.

title: nasi goreng(indonesian fried rice)
directions: Combine chuck, bread crumbs, eggs, 1/2 cup onions, salt and pepper.
Form into tiny meat balls; set aside.
In large Dutch oven, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Add 1 1/2 cups onions and celery; saute until golden.
Remove from pan.
In same pan, brown meat balls, keeping them round by rotating pan.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Add curry, 2 teaspoons salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and broth; bring to boil.
Add rice; cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add celery-onion mixture, shrimp and rice to meat balls in pan.
Cover; heat until hot.
Serve in same Dutch oven or heaped on platter.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in order given and fold in Cool Whip last.	Chill for several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Will fit into medium bowl.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Line
vanilla
wafers
on
bottom
of
bowl
and around bottom.
Pour pineapple over vanilla wafers, then pour vanilla pudding over pineapple.
Repeat this step 3 times and top with Cool Whip.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, salt, milk, egg yolks and vanilla. Cook over medium heat until thick. Stir continuously. Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture. Beat 1/4 cup sugar with egg whites until it stands in peaks. Pour into dish and brown in 375° oven.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken; dice.
Mix mushroom soup, green onions, celery, bell pepper and pimento.
Add cheese and chicken.
Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Combine onion and oil in saucepan and heat. Add broccoli and cook 5 minutes.
Add can of soup and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and stir in Cheez Whiz and milk.
Add salt and cook 3 minutes or until bubbly.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix rice and sauce. Pour into lightly buttered casserole dish.
Cover and heat about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday ham ball
directions: Mix all together except nuts.
Roll in ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: susan smith's cheese soup
directions: Combine the 4 cups of water and bouillon; heat until dissolved.
Add onions, celery and potatoes.
Cook 10 minutes. Add California vegetable mix (broccoli, cauliflower and carrots); cook 10 minutes.
Mix cream soups with water; add to mix and heat thoroughly.
Add Velveeta; heat until melted on low heat so as not to scorch.
Makes a large amount.

title: six layer casserole
directions: Place potatoes, celery, ground beef, onions, green pepper and tomatoes in layers in greased 2-quart casserole, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper.
Garnish with green pepper rings. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: polish sausage and potato casserole
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed on package.
Slice sausages thin. Add vegetables and sausage to potatoes.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: honey sesame chicken
directions: Let the chicken sit in the honey, turn over to moisten both sides.
Then dip into the sesame seeds.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1 hour in a 325 degree oven.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine butter and garlic; set aside.
Combine crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Dip each breast in butter mixture and coat with crumbs.
Roll tightly and skewer with toothpicks. Arrange rolls in a shallow baking dish.
Add lemon juice to the remaining butter and garlic mixture; drizzle over chicken rolls. Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove toothpicks before serving.

title: rigatoni ala carbonara
directions: Heat the oil and saute the bacon and garlic.
As soon as garlic is brown, discard.
Cook pasta until tender but still firm.

title: sweet potato custard pie
directions: Prepare unbaked pie shell.
Peel and boil potato.
Drain and mash with margarine.
Beat in sugar, flour, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk; beat well.
Pour filling into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: apple bake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Mix and sift other 6 dry ingredients together; add to egg mixture.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts and 2 cups chopped apples (do not peel).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: tomato juice supreme
directions: Cook tomatoes, onion, bell pepper and celery until done. Remove from heat; cool and strain.
Return juice to stove.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: jocelyn's crab quiche
directions: If you wish
to freeze, precook pie shell before adding mixture.
Mix all
ingredients, pour into pie shell, refrigerate overnight.	Bake
at
350°	until center is firm, approximately 1 hour.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute onion in margarine until browned.
Add 1 cup water and potatoes.
Boil gently about 10 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender.
Add fish and succotash and cook 5 minutes, until fish flakes and vegetables are tender.
Stir in milk, parsley, dill weed, salt and pepper.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: skinny chili
directions: Fry meat in a skillet coated with Pam. Drain any fat from the meat. Drain beans but do not rinse them. Add beans, Mexican sauce and tomatoes to the meat and stir. Cook slowly until mixture is hot. Serve in bowls. Sprinkle with shredded Alpine Lace cheese and chopped tomato. Add chopped onion to the top, too. Add hot sauce to taste.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and zucchini.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Place in buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: gourmet rice
directions: Slowly saute noodles in butter until brown.
Add chicken soup, water, onion mix and rice; stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat, cover until all water is absorbed.
Serve.
(Freezes nicely.)

title: fudge sauce(for biscuits)
directions: Boil butter, sugar and milk.
Add vanilla and cocoa.
Cool.

title: buckeye balls
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Mix margarine, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla with hands to make a smooth dough (very stiff). Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Put into refrigerator for 1/2 hour or until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and Crisco in double boiler.
Using round toothpick prick center of cookie and dip into chocolate so 3/4 of ball is coated.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 60.
They freeze well.

title: apple pumpkin butter
directions: Put all ingredients into a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally until it is as thick as pudding.
Scrape into jars; cool.
Cover and refrigerate.
Great for gift giving.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: In large bowl combine cake mix, 1 egg, margarine and 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
In large bowl beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in condensed milk then remaining 2 eggs, pumpkin, 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.
Mix well. Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Chill.

title: applesauce doughnuts
directions: Mix egg and Sweet 'N Low together.
Add vanilla, butter and applesauce.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to applesauce mixture.
Stir by hand.
Place dough in a bowl or on wax paper. Chill and roll out 1/2-inch on a lightly floured board.
Cut out with a floured cutter.
Heat oil; fry several at a time.
Drain on paper towels.
Can be frozen.

title: chef dan's "no peeking" pasta
directions: Cook pasta until tender; drain and mix with 2 tablespoons olive oil. In a separate pan, saut garlic with 1 tablespoon of olive oil. When garlic is golden brown, add white wine and cook until almost dry. Add heavy cream and cook for 5 minutes on medium heat. Add Mozzarella cheese until thick. Add tomatoes, spinach, salt, pepper and cumin. Place sauce over pasta; mix well and serve.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moist.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into three greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool completely.

title: sea island salad
directions: Stir mayonnaise, sour cream and seasoning into cooked macaroni.
Gently stir in peas and remaining ingredients and chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks and add oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Cook in waffle iron.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake in greased pan at 350° until done.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil raisins and apples in water 3 minutes and cool.
Add rest and mix well.
Refrigerate a couple hours and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix well. Add flour sifted with salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Make small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no-rise pizza dough
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, salt and shortening with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Add 3 cups more flour.
Knead into 2 balls and roll onto greased pizza pan.
Add toppings.
Bake at 375° until crust is golden brown.
Makes 2 regular or 1 deep dish pizza.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Mix all together. Heat broiler and spread on party sized rye or pumpernickel slices and broil about 3 minutes, until browned.

title: cheese balls
directions: Work all ingredients until well blended.
Let set overnight (or all afternoon) in refrigerator.
After mixture becomes firm, shape into ball.
Roll in crushed nuts, parsley flakes or paprika. Can be molded, then refrigerate again.
This recipe makes about 3 large cheese balls.
Can be divided.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: In #3-sized Rubbermaid container, place graham crackers (no need to break).
Add bananas.
Mix milk and pudding mix together until thickened.
Add sour cream and whipped topping; mix well. Pour over graham crackers and bananas.
This will just about fill container.
Cover.
Place in refrigerator 24 hours before eating for flavors to blend.

title: my favorite apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and cut apples in slices and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been buttered. Work together with a fork, pastry blender or fingers the remaining ingredients until crumbly. Spread over the apples and bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour.
Test apples with fork to be sure they are cooked. Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Place melted butter and dry ingredients in bottom of 11 x 8 x 2-inch ovenproof dish.
Cut squash in 1/2-inch slices and place in dish.
Arrange apples on top.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lisbon's garlic grits
directions: Cook grits according to directions on box.
Add butter and cheese and stir until melted.
Add eggs, beaten with the milk. Stir until well blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake in 400 oven for 8 minutes, cool. Mix cream cheese, sugar, Cool Whip. Spread on cool pretzel crust. Dissolve jello in water, mix in the strawberries.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Pour jello mixture on top of cream cheese. Let chill overnight.

title: confederate hamburger pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix together beef, crumbs and seasonings. Stir in one-half of the tomato sauce.
Spread meat mixture in ungreased 10-inch pie pan.
Pour on top another one-half of the tomato sauce and spread.
Add the beans and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13x9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, water, eggs and mayonnaise.
Blend well as directed.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into churn.
Add milk until the churn is 3/4 full.
Freeze in ice cream churn until firm.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Combine oyster liquid, butter, salt, pepper, cream and sherry.

title: kielbasa soup
directions: Make soup according to can directions. Add all other ingredients. Amounts are according to personal taste.
To reduce fat content, precook sausage and bacon. Drain fat, then add to soup.
Of course, this may be increased by using more green pea soup.

title: chicken breast scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken breasts into 2 x 1-inch pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Add garlic, scallions, parsley, dill, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper. Cook for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake for 10 minutes. Turn chicken and bake another 10 minutes, then broil for 3 to 4 minutes until lightly browned.

title: shipwreck
directions: Grease small roaster or baking dish with lid.
Place sliced potatoes in bottom. Season, then layer ground beef, season, onion, celery, rice, beans and soup over top.
Add 1/2 to 2/3 can water from soup can.
Cover.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramels
directions: Stir the above ingredients together.
Microwave 15 minutes on High, then stir.
Microwave 15 minutes on Medium-high; stir again. Microwave 10 minutes on Medium-high.
It should be done.
Test by dropping in cold water; when a solid ball forms, it is done.
Pour into 2 large buttered cake pans.
Cut into pieces and wrap in wax paper after it is cold.

title: frosty lime punch
directions: Combine ice cream and sherbet together with potato masher.
Add juice and Sprite.
Beat on low speed with mixer until creamy. Serve immediately.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Uncover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until slightly browned and firm. Serves 8.

title: oven stew
directions: Put ingredients in Dutch oven. Cover and bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry crumbled hamburger and sausage, drain.
Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Add chopped onions and peppers.
Then add 1/2 pizza sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Add 1/2 macaroni mixture, 1/2 meat, 1/2 mushrooms, 1/2 pepperoni and 1/2 cheese.
Then repeat all steps until you have completed second layer.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with rolls and salad.

title: potato pizza supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef in pan.
Add all ingredients, but tomato sauce and cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour tomato sauce over; bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Add cheese on top; return to oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: beat-the-holiday-rush beans
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan, break turkey into chunks; add onion, garlic and 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Stir often over medium-high heat until liquid evaporates and meat and onion start to brown.
Add another 1/2 cup broth.
Stir to release browned bits.
Boil dry as in preceding step.
Repeat, adding liquid and boiling dry until meat and onion are well browned, 2 or 3 more times.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups broth, kidney, lima and pinto beans, garbanzo, catsup, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Cover and simmer gently until flavors are blended, about 1 hour.
Stir often.
If making ahead, let cool. Cover and chill up to 3 days.
Reheat to serve.
Serves 6.

title: baked elegant chicken breasts
directions: Combine sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, garlic salt and lemon juice in bowl.
Place stuffing mix in separate bowl.
Coat chicken with sour cream mixture and then roll chicken in the stuffing mix.
Place chicken in buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: basic eggnog
directions: Put ingredients except nutmeg into blender. If using electric mixer, put ingredients into deep narrow bowl.
If using blender, cover and run on high speed.
If using mixer, beat on high until blended.
Pour into serving glasses; sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.
Makes 3 cups.

title: fruit salad chantilly
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling.
Add to gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water, orange rind and lemon juice. Chill until partially set.
Fold fruit cocktail into gelatin mixture, then fold in Cool Whip.
Turn into a 6-cup mold and chill until firm.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat together butter and 1/2 cup sugar in a bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat yolks in one at a time and add sifted dry ingredients, alternately with buttermilk to egg yolk mixture, starting and ending with dry ingredient mixture and beating well after each addition.
Beat until smooth.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour.
This recipe makes 2 pies.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together well. Pour in the graham cracker crust
and refrigerate overnight.

title: miniature date and nut cupcakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in 24 miniature tins.
Spray tins with Pam.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: crab
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spread onto English muffins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Add roasted (peeled) garlic to cooked peas and puree in a food processor.
Add stock, mustard, vinegar, sugar and olive oil. Taste for salt, pepper and vinegar, and add if needed.
Stir in red onions.
Chill.
Serve with pita wedges and fennel sticks for dipping.

title: waffles
directions: In a bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Add milk and butter or lard.
Stir.
Pour into hot waffle iron.

title: orange or lime punch
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and 2 cups warm water until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: palomino fudge
directions: Butter sides of 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, milk and salt.
Heat and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to boiling.
Cook to soft ball stage, 238°, stirring only as necessary.
Remove from heat, add margarine and cool to 110°, without stirring.
Add vanilla, beating vigorously until candy begins to hold shape.
Add marshmallow cream.
Beat until very thick and beginning to lose gloss.
Quickly stir in cherries and spread in buttered shallow pan or dish.
Score in squares while warm.
Cut when firm.
Makes about 24 pieces.

title: pepparkakor(swedish ginger cookies)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
When well creamed, add all dry ingredients.
Roll out very thin and cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes to a light brown. Remove to cooling racks.

title: plain cookie recipe(christmas cookies)
directions: Take the cookie dough; slice on the little lines of dough so you will know where to cut them.
Use bears and Christmas tree cutters.
Put them in the oven.
They show on cookie dough how long to cook.
Eat them!

title: skillet corn saute
directions: In 10-inch skillet, blend savory herb with garlic soup mix and water.
Stir in corn and red pepper.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer covered 5 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in green onions.
Makes about 8 servings.
Good with roasted chicken.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl; beat for 20 minutes at medium speed.
Pour cake into ungreased tube pan.
Put into a cold oven, turn heat on to 350° and bake for 1 hour.
Do not open door during baking.
Test doneness.
Cool in pan.
This cake freezes well.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and crackers.
Crumble Ritz crackers and place on top of casserole with cheese.
Pour melted margarine on top of crackers.
Bake at 325° until brown (about 45 minutes).

title: homemade hot salsa
directions: In a medium sized bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Cover and let stand in refrigerator for several hours. Salsa will get hotter the longer it stands.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter and put a small amount in bottom of 9 X 13 glass dish, pour remainder into bowl and add all other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: summer vegetable casserole
directions: Slice vegetables in casserole dish in order given.
Dot each layer with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
(Add no water; will make its own juice.)
It will cook down so fill to top.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown.
Drain well.
Spread bread cubes in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.

title: granny's unexpected grandkids' lunch
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper with seasonings; drain.
Add beans, Ro-Tel and soup; mix together.
Layer tortillas and meat mixture in large casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, cover with grated cheese.
Cook until cheese is completely melted.

title: seafood roll-ups
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Cut fish into 4 portions.
Make 4 rectangles.
In a bowl, combine cheese, chives, pimento, salt and pepper. Spread the mixture on the fish. Roll up fillets around filling.
Place seam side down in a loaf pan that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Combine the bread crumbs and paprika.
Brush fish with the 1 tablespoon yogurt and sprinkle with the bread crumb mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until the fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: sue nutt's potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes into bite size pieces and boil 5 minutes.
Drain and put in large crock-pot.
In large saucepan melt butter, add flour and stir.
Add milk and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook until thickened.
Add cubed cheese and stir until melted. Pour cheese sauce over potatoes and cook on low setting for 3 to 4 hours.
Do not stir.
Very good!

title: cinnamon apple butter
directions: Combine all except spices.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add spices.
May be canned or frozen.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream together cheese and margarine. Add remaining ingredients. Form into balls. Press flat. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp or scallop scampi genovese
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
If scallops are large, cut in half. Begin heating the water and plan to have the pasta ready when the scampi is finished.
Heat olive oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.
Add the chopped garlic and saute lightly until slightly golden.
Add the tomato sauce, parsley, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the shrimp or scallops and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until cooked.
Do not over cook or they will be tough.
Serve over the pasta.
Serves 4.

title: lemon sugar cookies
directions: In bowl, beat sugar and butter until fluffy.
Mix in eggs, lemon peel and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt. Form into 4 disks, wrap and chill 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°. Roll dough 3/16 of an inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutter; place on baking sheet.
In as many cups as colors used, mix 1 egg yolk with 1 teaspoon water and food color.
Brush onto cookies and top with sprinkles.
Bake 8 minutes until set. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil, and shape into patties. Fry in deep hot oil until browned.
Drain on paper towels.

title: fruited pork salad
directions: In jar with tight fitting lid, shake first 5 ingredients (juice, vinegar, oil, honey and dry mustard).
Use large nonstick skillet and spray with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat to medium-hot.
Stir pork slices 3 to 4 minutes until done.
Put lettuce in individual plates. Top with pork and fruit. Spoon dressing over salads.

title: ravioli and spinach primavera
directions: Prepare spinach according to package directions; set aside. Prepare broccoli mixture according to package directions, using 1/4 cup water.
Drain vegetables and place in large serving bowl; keep warm.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. When cake is almost completely cooled, pour on frosting.

title: hot and spicy cider
directions: Add all ingredients in a large pot.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Drain cider from allspice, cloves and cinnamon stick. Serve hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Put beans into a baking dish.
Add all of ingredients except bacon.
Mix well.
Put bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken, reserving broth.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add flour and make a paste.
Slowly add cream and enough broth for thin gravy consistency.
Pepper and salt to taste and simmer.
Cut up chicken and add veggies to a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Pour gravy over chicken and veggies.
Cover with dough.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
For one serving, use 2 rounded teaspoonfuls of mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: chess pie
directions: Prepare unbaked pie shell.
Mix butter and sugar and simmer slowly, stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly, stirring constantly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla, salt and vinegar; mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Shake pie gently.
It is done when center gives slightly.

title: manicotti crepes(crespelle)
directions: These crepes are very light and can be used with any of the fillings in this book.

title: orange breakfast ring
directions: Combine sugar and orange rind.
Separate biscuits.
Dip each in butter and coat with sugar mixture.
Stand biscuits on side, overlapping edges in a 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: won ton soup(serves 6)
directions: In a bowl, combine egg yolk, bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon onion, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef.
Mix well.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in an oblong pan.
Cover with dry cake mix.
Smooth cake mix and make even.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pear congealed salad
directions: Put pear juice in jello and bring to a boil.
Mash pears and cut cream cheese into small pieces.
Pour all of this into dish. Let set to semi hard, then add Cool Whip and fold in.
Return to refrigerator to finish setting.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: *Soak poppy seed in milk for 20 minutes before adding to batter.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with whole graham crackers, breaking crackers if necessary.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Let stand 5 minutes;
then blend in Cool Whip.
Spread half the pudding mixture over the crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Top with pudding mixture and remaining crackers. spread remaining pudding mixture over top layer of crackers. Chill 3 hours.

title: honey banana bread(negligible cholesterol)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add walnuts.
Combine bananas, lemon juice, honey and milk.
Add flour mixture, a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Pour into lightly oiled baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° or until done.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 1 1/2 hours and serve.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and white pepper in bag.
Shake pieces of chicken in bag to coat. Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Brown chicken in oil. When chicken is almost browned, add onion and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar and garlic.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until tender, about 30 minutes.
Add a little water if it becomes dry.
Serve hot with cooked spaghetti. Serves 4.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, saute bacon and chopped onion until clear.
Combine spaghetti sauce, beef broth, water, basil, salt and pepper and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add vegetables and simmer 10 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: sweet buns
directions: Measure water.
Add yeast and set aside.
Place milk, salt, sugar and shortening in saucepan; scald.
Place flour in a large pan.
Mix cooled milk mixture with some of the flour.
Add yeast and knead.
Set aside, covered, until it is doubled.
Knead and make rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: applesauce
directions: After you have made your jelly
from the cooked apples, press them through a sifter to get the pulp
out and the peels also. Add sugar until sweet and cinnamon.
Pour into jars and cover them.
Now it is ready to eat!

title: english cheese strottle
directions: Remove crusts from bread and dice.
Mix with grated cheese and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk and seasonings. Add bread/cheese mixture and let stand 1/2 hour.
Lay partially cooked and drained sausage in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture over sausage.
Place baking dish into a large dish with water around it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown and fluffy.

title: great south bay crab bisque
directions: Steam live crabs 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and pick out crabmeat.
Melt butter, add flour.
Add milk and bring to simmer. Cook until a little thick.
Chop eggs, add with crabmeat.
Simmer a few minutes (3 to 5).
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to simmer and serve.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: lemon babka easter bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Heat milk, butter and water until very warm. Butter does not need to melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add egg yolks and 1/2 cup of the flour.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
With spoon, stir in remaining flour. Cover.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour or more.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Cream together oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy, then add flour, soda and salt.
Mix this well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
This is a heavy batter.

title: vegetable steaks
directions: Drain steaks and mushrooms, reserving juice.
Dip steaks in beaten egg and bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until brown.
Saute onions, mushrooms, almonds and parsley.
Alternate layers of steaks, onions and mushrooms in casserole dish.
Combine 1 cup of juice with sour cream; pour over casserole.
Add milk, if necessary.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly and top is lightly browned.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: beer batter bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and beer in bowl.
Stir to blend.
Turn into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Melt butter and pour half over dough. Continue to bake another 40 minutes.
Serve warm with butter or cool and slice, then toast slices and serve with butter.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: grandma's best meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Form into a loaf. Place bacon on top of loaf.
Place meat loaf in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: party mix
directions: Melt oleo.
Add salts and sauce.
Pour over cereal mixture. Mix real well.
Put in pans and heat in oven at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together except marshmallows.
Mix enough milk so that it is easy to stir but not thin.
Put marshmallows on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple-coconut cake
directions: Mix first
ingredients.
Pour
into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: no bake cereal cookies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter until smooth.
Mix in cornflakes.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Crumble Blue cheese and place all ingredients in bowl.
Beat well with fork and spoon.
Do not use other device, will make watery.

title: curried squash and pear bisque
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Halve the squash; bake (cut side down) on baking sheet for 45 minutes or until tender. Cool, peel and mash. Set aside (approximately 3 1/2 cups).

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place spoonfuls of mixture on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cracker jack
directions: Mix sugars, syrup and margarine; bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cream of tartar and salt.
Pour over popped corn.
Put in large roast pan and bake 1 hour at 200°. Pour onto waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: mushroom steak
directions: More wild rabbits are taken by hunters each year in this country than any other type of game, big or small.
The annual number totals over 45,000,000.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Boil raisins in water 5 minutes. Drain raisins and add to mixture.
Bake in a greased pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
While warm, add cranberry sauce. Let mixture cool.
Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes.
Fold in sour cream.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on bed of lettuce.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix sour cream and coconut; add fruit and stir until well mixed.

title: corn breaded fish bake
directions: If necessary, cut fillets to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Then cut into about 4 x 1-inch strips.
Cover and refrigerate until needed.
In a large mixing bowl stir together the cornmeal, soda and salt.
Stir in 1 cup of the cheese and the chili peppers.
In another mixing bowl, combine eggs, buttermilk, oil and hot pepper sauce.
Beat egg mixture with a rotary beater until well combined, then add it to the cornmeal mixture.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Spread half of the batter in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place fish in rows on top of batter.
Then spread remaining batter over fish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 450° oven about 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in cornbread center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake for 1 to 2 minutes more or until melted.
To serve, cut into squares and top with warm Green Chili Salsa.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: blueberry muffin
directions: Beat together first three ingredients.
Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder and add to first mixture.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and chill.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine sugar, 1 stick melted oleo and graham cracker crumbs; mix well.
Line a 9 x 12-inch dish with crumbs.
Combine 2 sticks oleo, extract and powdered sugar; beat with electric mixer for 15 minutes on medium speed.
Pour over crumbs.
Layer remaining ingredients, in order, over filling.
Garnish top with strawberries.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serves 12.

title: pea salad
directions: Boil peas in butter until done. Strain.
Chop onions in small pieces. Chop eggs in small pieces.
Mix in a bowl with Miracle Whip and mustard.
Use salt and pepper to taste.
Let chill, then serve.

title: hot butter rum batter
directions: Heat in large saucepan butter, brown sugar and powdered sugar. When mixed well, add ice cream and vanilla.
Ready to serve.
Add 1 tablespoon or so to cup of hot water.
Serve with or without rum. May dust with nutmeg or serve with cinnamon stick.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine fruits and melted butter.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and curry powder; add to fruit and mix lightly.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple deeeeee-light
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package and set aside.

Using a 12 x 7 x 2-inch Pyrex dish, put a layer of graham crackers on bottom, a layer of pineapple next, followed by a layer of prepared pudding. Repeat this process, ending with a layer of crackers on top.
This can be served immediately or refrigerated for later use.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: pasta fagioli soup(country:  italian)
directions: Saute garlic and onions in olive oil in a large sauce or soup pan until soft.
Add beans, spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, parsley, salt, pepper, oregano and rosemary.
Simmer for 1 hour, covered. Cook pasta for 8 to 10 minutes in boiling water and add small amounts at a time.
Add Parmesan cheese.
If soup is too thick, add water.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: eggplant caviar
directions: Wrap whole eggplant in foil and bake at 350°, until soft. Cool, peel and chop up, seed and all.
In skillet, cover bottom with oil.
Chop garlic and brown.
Add chopped onion and saute until soft.
Then add eggplant.
Cook for about half and hour. Add to tomatoes, chopped.
Put juice from lemon, salt and pepper. Stir gently.
Simmer until well blended.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mary sue's chicken
directions: Put oil in bottom of baking dish.
Put dried beef in bottom of pan.
Place chicken on top of dried beef.
Put 1/2 slice of raw bacon on each piece of chicken.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together in a large casserole dish, buttered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pasta salad
directions: Mix tomato soup, oil, sugar and vinegar.
Reserve 1 cup sauce. Pour remaining sauce over pasta/vegetable mixture.
Add remaining cup of sauce the next day and serve.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add vegetables and cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: meat loaf with fruit
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and press into oiled or buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine cooking oil and sugar and beat well.
Add hot water. Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla and beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in 3 greased 8-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use light icing if you want, but it is good as is.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat in shortening.
Make space in bowl to beat eggs.
Add juice; gradually mix in flour mixture.
Add cranberries and orange peel. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 greased loaf pans.

title: breakfast caramel rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Place pecans in the bottom, then place rolls evenly in pan.
Melt butter or margarine with sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle the pudding onto the rolls.
Pour the melted butter mix over this and let stand overnight (8 to 10 hours). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Immediately turn onto a plate.

title: red baron pepperoni pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Remove pizza from the box and inner wrapper and place on preheated cookie sheet. Bake for 16 to 18 minutes or until center cheese is melted and edges are golden brown.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put nuts on 11 by 15 jelly roll pan in oven to warm.
Meanwhile, make meringue by beating egg whites; adding sugar and salt.
Fold nuts into meringue.
Melt butter in same jelly roll pan.
Spread nut mixture in melted butter.	Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
They are done when nuts are dry, brown and crispy.
Store in tin and place in refrigerator or freeze.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put first four ingredients in 2-quart pan.
Bring to a boil. Let boil 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla until peanut butter is melted.
Add oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool completely and serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour, oil, soda, salt and sugar; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, mix 1/2 cup water and yeast; add sour milk.
Mix well with dry ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours before using. Use as needed.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crumble cooked sausage; drain.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Scatter bread cubes in a baking dish.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese over bread. Pour eggs and milk mixture over.
Cover.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss all ingredients until thoroughly mixed. Serves 2.

title: can-can cassie
directions: Mix ingredients and top with noodles.
Dot with margarine. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: great turkey recipe
directions: To the chicken broth, add all ingredients except broccoli/peas.
Cook until carrots are tender.
Combine milk and flour in a separate bowl and then add quickly to the broth.
Bring to a boil and stir until broth thickens.
Add broccoli/peas.
If desired, bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with biscuits and/or rice.

title: broccoli a la quadras
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes in salted, boiling water; drain well. Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion and grated cheese.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour into baking dish and cover with crushed cheese crackers.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: clam dip
directions: Melt butter over low to medium heat. Add cream cheese, stirring.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place
sliced
apples
in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix remaining dry ingredients
and
eggs
until crumbly.
Pour over apples, then pour salad oil over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Put in sterilized jars and seal. Makes 4 pints.
Delicious on hot dogs or just by itself.

title: no-fat brandy slush
directions: Boil water.
Swish tea bags through boiling water.
Add orange juice and lemonade.
Add brandy.
Place in freezer (I put it in a 5-quart ice cream pail).
Stir occasionally for 24 hours.
To use, fill a glass with slush; add 7-Up (diet or regular).
If you are having an extremely good day or extremely bad day, add more brandy.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast dissolved in warm water.
Mix until flour is moist.
Place in a covered bowl in refrigerator.
When ready to cook, take out amount needed.
Roll out 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut sirloin steak into 2 inch strips.
In a large skillet brown the steak in the butter.
Add the onions; cook until limp.
Stir in gravy and tomato paste.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 10 to 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Slowly stir in sour cream.
Serve over buttered noodles.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, sugar, lemon juice, celery and salt.
Fold mayonnaise into whipped cream.
Gently fold cream mixture into apple mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: beefy biscuits casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck well; drain all fat.
Stir vegetables, brown gravy mix, water and Mrs. Dash together with meat in shallow casserole (11 x 13-inch).
Cut biscuits into fourths and place on top of meat mixture.
(Push down to coat with gravy; will rise back up as baked.)
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes, or until biscuits are browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato patties(50 years old)
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes in rounds.
Fry in a skillet with bacon drippings.
Cook on medium heat until tender.

title: mint angel cake
directions: Beat egg whites in a small mixing bowl until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar; beat until soft peaks form.
Fold in flavorings.
Gradually beat in sugar; continue beating until stiff. Sift cake flour into egg whites and fold in very gently.
Bake in an ungreased 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oven parmesan cheese
directions: Mix ingredients, except chicken.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then roll in crumb mixture.
Place in shallow baking dish; bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and put into loaf pan.
Put ketchup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch together.
Then add balance of ingredients.
Cook until thick and then add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Cool and put in crust.
Use white for meringue.

title: pull-apart rolls
directions: Break first roll into bite size pieces so they don't touch each other.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts.
Heat milk, butter, brown sugar and pudding mix until well blended.
Pour half over bottom layer of dough.
Repeat with second roll of dough.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nuts on top.
Let raise approximately 2 hours.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms with a damp cloth.
Leave whole or slice lengthwise, stems and all.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add mushrooms and cook 6 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve on buttered toast.
Good with steak or other meats.

title: potato bud gnocchi
directions: Melt butter in hot water; add Potato Buds and mix.
Stir in egg.
Add sifted salt, baking powder and flour.
Knead until smooth.
Form into rope strips.
On floured board, cut into 1-inch pieces.
Make a finger indentation with finger and ready to cook or place on waxed-lined cookie sheet to freeze.
When frozen well, bag in plastic bags.
They keep well until ready to use.

title: banana pudding
directions: Fold (don't beat) the first 4 ingredients together.
Layer as usual.

title: pear pie
directions: Arrange pear halves or sliced pears in unbaked pie shell.
Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Add cream mixture.
Blend and pour over pears.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until cream is set.

title: curried sauce for turkey or chicken
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Saute garlic, onion and pepper for 5 minutes.
Stir in curry powder and saute for 1 minute more. Stir in flour and gradually add chicken broth and cream.
Stir over low heat until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Season to taste and add salt and pepper.
Serve with cooked, sliced turkey or chicken.
Makes 2 cups.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork chops, simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool, pour over pork chops in bowl.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Arrange chops in shallow baking pan; pour sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with sauce occasionally.
Yields 2 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti per package directions.
Drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a buttered 10-inch pie plate. Cook beef, onion and pepper until vegetables are tender and meat is browned in a large skillet.
Drain.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar and seasonings.
Spread Ricotta cheese over bottom of "crust."
Fill pie with tomato mixture. Cover with foil and chill in refrigerator for 2 to 24 hours.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with Mozzarella. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag add potatoes, oil and soup mix.
Empty into baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until potatoes are tender and brown.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together with a spoon.
Flour and grease tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix all ingredients and shake several times a day until sugar is completely dissolved and mixture no longer separates.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes by scalding them briefly in boiling water so skin comes	off
easily.
Peel
garlic and put into blender with a small
piece
of
peeled
tomato.
Blend for 2 seconds. Add rest of tomatoes
to
garlic
mixture and blend for 2 to 3 seconds. Remove and	place
in pot.	Bring to a simmer uncovered.
Add bay leaves
and
basil	to
the sauce.	Simmer for about 5
minutes. Remove
and
discard bay leaves.
Add olive oil just before serving.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Partially melt chocolate candy bars in double boiler; remove from heat and beat until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts. Spread in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill, then cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour over cracker crumbs.
Pour over broccoli mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl cream together molasses, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix, put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients together as listed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Yield:
1 large loaf.

title: cherry surprise balls
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add flour and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Chill dough for several hours.
Mold dough around cherries, covering completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Roll warm balls in powdered sugar; place on rack to cool.

title: seasoned black-eyed peas
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Add water, if necessary. Garnish with pimientos, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, soda and salt. Fold in quick oats and then corn flakes.

title: chili-sausage supper
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until noodles are tender, adding more water if needed to prevent sticking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: butterfinger candy dessert
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg yolks until blended.
Add egg yolks and blend until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and blend.
Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Put a layer of cake in a bowl, pour half of the creamed mixture over cake.
Crumble candy bars.
Add another layer of each, top with more candy bars.
Chill until served.
Pretty served in a tall, clear glass bowl.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except for potato chips and margarine. Place in glass casserole dish and top with margarine and chips mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside. Beat eggs and milk together.
Add dry ingredients and butter to milk and eggs mixture.
Cook slowly over stove eye until thickened, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and pour into pie shell.
Cool before refrigerating.
Top with whipped cream.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in oleo until tender but not brown.
Add broth and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Blend together the milk and flour before adding to vegetables.
Add cheese and parsley.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Serves 7 to 8 people.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix berries with flour and cinnamon.
If fruit is dry, sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over it.
Place in pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and cut a few slits in it. Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes until crust is nicely browned and juice begins to bubble through slits.
A favorite of my mother, Elsie Paulus.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs which have been beaten and crushed bananas.
Sift flour and soda; add to mixture.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake in loaf pan 40 minutes.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in skillet.
Cover and cook for 1 minute.
Uncover and cook, turning until barely tender, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make pie pastry. Roll thin into 7-inch squares. Pare and core desired number of medium-sized apples. Mix 1/2 c. sugar and 1 1/2 tsp. cinnamon. Fill cavities of apples with mixture; dot with butter. Place each apple on a square of dough; wrap apples with dough and seal. Place in baking dish. Prepare butter syrup as directed below.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Combine all
ingredients in a double boiler; cook until thickened and smooth.
(One
or
two
tablespoons of brandy or whiskey may be added.)

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix powder sugar, butter and flour.
Spread on a 13 inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: meat and macaroni salad
directions: Combine meat or tuna fish, celery, macaroni, salt, pepper and chopped, cooked eggs.
Add salad dressing and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate a few hours before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs together.
Next add all of the remaining ingredients.
Batter will be soupy.
Drop 1/4 cup batter or less on cookie sheet.
Six on a sheet.
Makes big cookies. Sprinkle with sugar or cinnamon sugar.
You can also drop raisins or butterscotch or chocolate bits on top.
You may need to lower heat in your oven.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: butter chocolate chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine cake mix, eggs and melted butter in large bowl. Stir until thoroughly blended. (Mixture will be stiff.) Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Press mixture evenly in greased pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Do not overbake. Cool completely. Cut into bars.

title: chocolate cherry upside-down cake
directions: Spread pie filling over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt. In another bowl, combine water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Add liquid ingredients to flour mixture all at once.
Stir well to moisten.
Pour batter over cherry pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes, then invert and cool completely.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: 7-up chicken
directions: In a large skillet cook chicken until tender in the margarine and soy sauce.
Then add remaining ingredients; cover with lid until heated through.
Serve with Chinese noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread into bits and cover with boiling water.
Let soak until consistency of cake batter.
Add egg and butter which has been melted in baking dish.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 375° until brown.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and place in buttered baking dish.
Combine pineapple juice and sugar, sage and flour with egg.
Cook until thickened.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and marshmallows over pineapple.
Top with sauce.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
This dish is very good with meats.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Stir in pizza sauce.
Drain mushrooms, oregano, garlic salt and onion.
Bring to a boil and remove.
Stir in pepperoni.
Combine sauce with cooked macaroni and the milk. Bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together (except crackers).
Put in casserole dish, that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put crackers on top.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: ann lander's meat loaf recipe
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan; cover with two strips of bacon, if you like that flavor.
Pour over all one 8 ounce can tomato sauce.
Bake one hour at 350°; serves six.

title: french-cut green bean casserole
directions: Make cream sauce of all but the green beans and cracker crumbs.
Pour sauce mixture over the green beans.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° only until bubbly.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Roll on floured board in rolls cut in equal parts; wrap in separate rolls in waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator; bake as needed at 350°.
Do not bake too brown, as they will be too hard.

title: man's meal
directions: Fry onion and pepper, add meat.
Brown 20 minutes.
In casserole, put meat mixture, soup, corn, olives and cooked spaghetti (drained).
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine avocados, salad dressing, onion and salt.
Mix well. Stir in bacon just before serving.
Serve with corn chips or party crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Heat to boiling, stirring until well mixed.
Pack into jars (pint) and cold pack at least 5 minutes.
Makes 8 pints or so.

title: angel kisses
directions: Let sugar stand with egg whites for 1/2 hour, then beat in electric mixer until mixture is stiff.
Add almond flavoring and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Bake in 250° oven for 40 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: zucchini and chilies
directions: Cook zucchini until tender, over medium heat.
Drain.
In a skillet, heat oil and saute onion.
Add tomatoes, green chiles and seasonings; blend well.
Cook for a few minutes over reduced heat. Add cheese; mix in well.
Cover; heat 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve when cheese is fully melted.
Serves 6.

title: chili
directions: Place butter in kettle. Add shredded onions and beef; stir until brown. Pour in soup and beans; cook 10 minutes. Make a paste of chili powder, water and flour. Add to mixture. Cook about 45 minutes or until done.

title: turkey in a sack
directions: Use a double-strength grocery sack.
Oil the inside of the sack and the turkey.
Salt and pepper.
Preheat oven to 325°. Slip turkey into sack and tie the top securely.
Be sure there is no hole in the sack.
Place turkey on a rack in a large pan.
Bake according to this time table: 12 pounds or under for 20 to 22 minutes per pound; 12 pounds or over for 16 to 18 minutes per pound.
When done, punch a few holes in the bottom of sack to let the juices run into the pan for the gravy.
Let turkey rest 20 minutes before carving.

title: lima bean and noodle soup
directions: Cook lima beans and noodles separately.
Drain the noodles and add them to the lima beans.
Add milk.
Season with salt, butter and cinnamon.

title: date drops
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift the dry ingredients.
Chop dates and nuts.
Mix with flour and add to first mixture.
Cookies must be stiff enough to drop from the tip of the spoon.
Drop on a buttered cookie sheet and bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp a la creole
directions: Dice shrimp.
Stew all the other ingredients in a casserole for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and serve hot on rounds of toasted bread.

title: baked banana peppers
directions: Wash peppers,
then dry and cut peppers in half lengthwise. Put in baking pan; add garlic salt.
Add 1 cup oil over them. Bake until golden brown.
Put in clean sterilized jars. Add vinegar mixture.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beef and macaroni bake
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper.
Brown ground beef.
Mix onion, pepper and beef.
Add cooked macaroni, soup and milk.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir until melted.
Pour into casserole dish and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well (with hands).
Mix once a day for 4 days (include day of preparation).
On 4th day, make into rolls approximately 2 inches in diameter.
Lay sausage rolls on pan so grease may drain in pan below.

title: okra stew
directions: Fry okra, chicken, onion and seasoning together until okra is not ropey.
After okra has fried, add corn, tomatoes, shrimp and tomato sauce together.
Cook until done.
Cook on low heat. Serves 9 to 12 people.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Sift flour.
Add salt and sift.
Beat eggs until light.
Add flour and 1/3 of the milk.
Continue beating for 30 seconds. Gradually add remaining milk.
Beat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Put 4 tablespoons drippings into pan, 7 1/2 x 12 x 2-inch.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve at once.
An accompaniment for roast beef.

title: hot broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions in a large saucepan; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
(Serve this in winter with fresh cornbread or crackers.)

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In a separate bowl, mix with fork the cake mix and 2 of the eggs.
Pour batter into pan over melted butter. Press lightly to all edges of pan. In a separate bowl, beat together with electric mixer the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Wait a few minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: Heat on low until all ingredients are dissolved and completely blended.
Dip the chicken in the sauce before placing on the grill and about every 15 minutes during cooking time.
May be refrigerated and used at a later time.

title: jiffy baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Casserole is done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: syl's catsup salad dressing
directions: Put lemon juice, vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, salt, pepper, onion, celery seed, turmeric and garlic in pan.
Bring to a boil. Turn down and simmer 2 minutes.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve on a crisp salad.
It is too heavy a sauce for Boston lettuce.
Good on thinly sliced cabbage with red and green peppers also thinly sliced.

title: gelatin special
directions: Mix whipped topping and dry jello together well, then add cottage cheese and pineapple which has been drained well.
Serve chilled.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk without stirring to soft-ball stage. Remove from heat; add peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Spread into buttered 8-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: cranberry marshmallow salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Fold in marshmallows and Whip 'n Chill.
Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray baking sheets with spray.
In a large bowl, combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves; set aside.
With mixer at low speed, cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and applesauce.
Stir in dry ingredients until smooth.
Drop cookie batter onto baking sheets by teaspoon.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 8 servings, 3 cookies each.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Saute onions and peppers in oleo 15 minutes.
Add peas, chicken broth and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
In a large dish, layer the spaghetti, mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Mix well; store in refrigerator.
Serve with apple wedges or any other fruit.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bake in regular size cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Layer graham crackers on cookie sheet (they should almost fit exactly).
Melt butter with sugar. Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan immediately and cool on waxed paper.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix well.
Soak overnight.
Bake on low heat in a 250° oven for 18 to 24 hours.

title: scone
directions: Mix by hand until well moistened.
Use greased loaf pan (will make 2 small loaves or 1 large loaf).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (so easy).
Good toasted with butter.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Remove leaves and trim base from cauliflower.
Wash.
Precook whole cauliflower in boiling salted water 12 to 15 minutes. Drain.
Place on ungreased shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread over cauliflower. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° approximately 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: golden upside-down snack bread(coffee cake)
directions: Grease a round 9 x 1 1/2-inch layer pan with shortening or margarine. Sprinkle bottom with brown sugar, almonds and coconut. Arrange fruit on top of sprinkled combination.
Stir biscuit mix, sour cream, sugar, melted margarine, egg and lemon juice in mixing bowl just until blended.
Beat well for about 30 seconds. Spread mixture evenly over fruit and bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool 5 minutes; turn out onto serving plate.
Serve with vanilla ice cream, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Combine chicken breasts, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, garlic powder, salt, pepper and onion-celery mixture and pour into shallow greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add fresh mushrooms, if desired.
Top with Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing.
Mix poppy seed and 1/2 stick melted butter or margarine and spread on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spring vegetable medley(microwave recipe)
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole for 30 seconds.
Combine asparagus, basil and pepper in casserole; mix well.
Cover; cook 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms; mix well.
Cover; cook 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in salt.
Cover; let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: turkey piccata
directions: Mix together flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge cutlets in flour mixture.
Heat oil and butter in skillet.
Add cutlets and saute until browned and cooked, about 2 minutes.
Remove and keep warm. Add broth, lemon juice and lemon slices to skillet; bring to boil. Return cutlets to skillet.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes. Just before serving, sprinkle with parsley.

title: mini pecan pies
directions: You will need nonstick mini muffin pans.

title: easy casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to box directions and set aside.
Cook onion in skillet and add crumbled ground beef and brown.
Combine tomato paste, cheese, beef/onion mixture and macaroni in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, water and salt, stirring frequently. Cook until clear.
Add jello; stir until jello is dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Halve or cut berries and add to mixture.
Place in baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.
To serve, top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: goulash casserole
directions: Boil macaroni according to directions, adding tomatoes and juice during boiling time.
When done, make sure only small amount of liquid is present (may have to drain some).
Stir in browned ground beef.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into lightly greased baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: layer jello
directions: Mix 1 box gelatin with 1 cup boiling water.
Divide into half. To first half, add 1/3 cup sour cream.
Mix well and pour into bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Refrigerate until firm about 1/2 hour.
Add 3 tablespoons cold water to remaining gelatin.
Pour over first layer.
Return to refrigerator and repeat 6 times.

title: julie's confetti spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage in butter; drain.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bojangles' biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco into dry ingredients, using a potato masher. Sprinkle buttermilk over mixture.
Work as little as possible.
Do not squeeze with hands.
Roll out dough.
Flour lightly on top. Cut.
Bake at 500° for 8 minutes.

title: brownie cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour, set aside.
Combine margarine, oil, water, and cocoa into saucepan, bring to a boil, pour over flour mixture.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk, mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9x13 pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 300 degrees.

title: apple salad mold
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and chill until partially set. Pour into mold.
Mix last 3 ingredients until smooth, then swirl through the gelatin mixture.
Chill.
Serve over crisp lettuce.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add potatoes; cook over low heat until tender.
Add soup and simmer.
Add cheese and cook until bubbly and melted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with a sprinkling of bacon bits on top.

title: perfect beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut fillet crosswise into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Cut each slice across grain into 1/2-inch wide strips. Slowly heat large heavy skillet.
In it melt 2 tablespoons butter. Add just enough beef strips to cover bottom of skillet.
Over high heat, sear quickly on all sides.
Remove beef as it browns (should be browned outside, rare inside).
Brown rest of beef; set aside. In remaining hot butter in same skillet, saute onion, garlic and mushrooms until onion is golden, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, beefer upper, ketchup, bay leaf, salt and pepper. Stir until smooth.
Gradually add beef broth; bring to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Over low heat, add wine, snipped dill and sour cream, stirring, until well combined. Add beef; simmer just until sauce and beef are hot.
Serve stroganoff with rice.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of dill or parsley over top.

title: hash brown surprise
directions: Thaw potatoes until workable.
Mix all ingredients except 3/4 of the butter.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with crumbs. Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 325° (about 1 hour) until golden and bubbly.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and place in a covered baking dish.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes or in microwave on High for about 2 to 3 minutes until hot.
Keep warm and serve with chips or crackers.
This dip usually disappears quickly!

title: banana salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and vinegar; simmer over low heat until thick.
Stir; set aside to cool.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed. Mix with the cooled mixture.
Layer mixture, bananas and peanuts, ending with the nuts on top.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 40 minutes or until the pie is done when knife comes out clean.

title: mom's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl until creamy.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken appetizers
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Cut bacon in thirds.
Secure bacon around small chicken pieces with toothpick.
Mix ketchup and brown sugar. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: colorful veggie bake
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package directions; drain. Place half in an ungreased 11 x 7 baking dish.

title: bugs
directions: Melt chips over double boiler.
Pour over noodles and nuts. Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Chill until firm. Hide in safe place.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla, sift dry ingredients together. Mix with chopped fruits and nuts and combine with creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoon on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Cook 15 minutes at 325°.
When done, cookies should be a light brown.
Makes about 8 dozen small cookies.
This may need to be mixed by hand.

title: grandma's short cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into cast-iron frying pan. Cook at 350° until golden brown.
Test like a cake layer.
