Great with fresh strawberries or peaches (sweeten).

title: chocolate raspberry dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine flour, sugar, 1/2 cup butter, baking powder and eggs in large bowl; beat until smooth. Add syrup; blend thoroughly. Pour batter in prepared pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Prepare Raspberry Cream Center and spread on cake. Cover; refrigerate until chilled.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1 cup sugar in skillet in 500° oven.
Mix together remaining sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk and eggs (beaten). Cook double boiler until thick.
Add melted sugar syrup.
Pour into baked, cooked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Combine chicken, apples, celery, grapes and 1/4 cup pecans in bowl.
Blend mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, mustard and Equal; stir into chicken mixture.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spoon salad onto lettuce-lined plates; sprinkle with 1/4 cup pecans, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine butter and flour in saucepan over low heat and brown lightly.
Slowly add chicken broth and milk until smooth and thickened.
Stir in chicken, mixed vegetables and peas.
Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Roll pastry real thin; cut in 1/2-inch strips.
Arrange in lattice design over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown.
You can make 2 layers of lattice on mixture.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Coat chicken in flour.
Melt butter in large skillet; place chicken skin side down and brown.
Add onions, garlic, parsley, salt, basil, water and tomato sauce.
Cover; simmer for 50 to 60 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Add mushrooms.
If necessary, add more water to sauce.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill for 2 hours or until ready to serve in covered container.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.

title: no-bake cookie balls
directions: In a double boiler over hot, not boiling water, melt chocolate; remove from heat.
Mix in syrup, 3 cups sugar, nuts, coffee (dissolved in the 1/3 cup hot water) and wafer crumbs.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in 1/2 cup sugar.
Store in covered container a day or so to ripen.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, then add pumpkin, salt, cinnamon, pumpkin spice and sugar.
Beat well.
Add milk and mix real good. Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top, then sprinkle nuts over top of cake mix.
Then pour melted butter evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness in center.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator.

title: easy fried rice
directions: Fix Rice-A-Roni per instructions on box.
Then scramble eggs and add
to rice.
Can be done in same pan if using stove top method.
Add cooked chicken and mix until heated thoroughly.

title: salad dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix in strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and place in freezer.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: lemonade
directions: Boil above ingredients for 5 minutes.
Let cool and add juice and 8 lemons.
Strain and store in refrigerator.
To make a drink, use 2 tablespoons of syrup per glass.
Try carbonated water.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook together all but the carrots.
After marinade is cooked together, add to carrots.
May be stored in refrigerator several days.

title: potluck chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup and sour cream; spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs, butter and celery seed; sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: apple torte
directions: Beat egg; add sugar.
Beat again.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to egg and sugar mixture, then add nuts and apples.
Grease and flour 9-inch pie tin.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Rinse chicken in water; do not dry off.
Mix flour and cheese. Heat 1 tablespoon butter in deep skillet with garlic; coat chicken in flour mixture.
Place in skillet and brown both sides (turning carefully).
It does not need to cook all the way through at this point.
Add more butter for each set of chicken you brown (depends on the size of skillet).
Place chicken carefully in a 9 x 13-inch serving dish that can go into oven.
Using same skillet, add 1 tablespoon butter and cook mushrooms for a couple of minutes, scraping bottom of skillet.
Add chicken broth, Marsala wine and cornstarch/water mixture (stir while adding cornstarch so it does not clump) and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Carefully pour broth mixture over chicken.
Cover and cook in heated oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Lower oven to keep warm for about 15 minutes or until ready to serve.

title: chicken pecan salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Stir well and chill several hours.
Add mayonnaise, grapes, apples and pecans; toss well.
Serve on lettuce.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Mash ripe bananas well and add, then add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: easy triple fudge cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
Blend dry cake mix into hot pudding.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Cook potatoes with their skins on until just tender.
Cool, peel and shred coarsely.
Mix cheese with melted oleo and add to potatoes.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in sour cream.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: *I use 1 date and 1 nut bread.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Spoon out batter with teaspoon for each cookie on wax paper.
Sprinkle with corn flake crumbs.
Roll each cookie until well coated.
Press to form cookie. Top with cherry cut in half.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: pam's irish bread
directions: Mixed fruit (candied) may be added for special occasions.

title: cheese ravioli with crab and garlic
directions: Cook ravioli according to package directions al dente. Drain. In a small skillet, saut garlic in oil over medium heat until it is pale gold, about 1 to 2 minutes, being careful not to burn it. Set aside.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread in the bottom of 9x13 pan. Cover that mixture with salsa, then layer cheese, lettuce (torn into small pieces), and black olives. Dip nacho chips and enjoy.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Separate batter evenly in 2 bread pans.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Outside of bread gets real brown.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and flour; toss to coat fruit. Add sugar and mix well.
Place in a two-quart buttered casserole dish (or use nonstick spray).
Combine oatmeal, cinnamon, allspice, brown sugar and melted margarine.
Spoon over fruit mixture.
Sprinkle pecan pieces on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: squash rolls
directions: Put butter, sugar, salt and squash in bowl; pour over hot milk, cool, add egg; add yeast and part of flour and beat well.
Add remaining flour; dough should not be too stiff, not as stiff as bread.
Let rise double or more.
Shape into rolls, put in pan, let rise again.
When ready for oven sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together margarine, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Combine oats, flour, salt, baking soda and chocolate chips.
Mix well. Place about 1/4 cup dough per cookie on greased baking sheet and bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix altogether and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter-pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix and frosting mix together.
Add oil, water and eggs.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: olive tarts
directions: Blend cheese with margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of this mixture around each olive, covering it completely.
To serve, bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: marinated garden salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the celery, cucumber, carrots and radishes.
Add the dressing and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Just before serving, add greens and toss.
Yields 5 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter until soft.
Add eggs and mix.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Don't forget to thaw frozen broccoli.
Mix by hand and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for about 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Beat well together.
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach skillet pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Pat into heavy skillet, letting dough hang over sides. Fill in with fresh peaches.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar, salt, cinnamon and butter.
Fold extra dough toward center, leaving center uncovered.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 25 minutes at 275°.

title: grilled pepperoni pizza sandwich
directions: Nonstick skillet is nice!

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: On top of stove, toast sesame seeds in pan with a dab of oil until light brown - Add to the remaining ingredients.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours or until thick.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given; drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven 12 to 14 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place in large pot (5 to 6-quart) and cook 3 to 4 hours over medium heat.
Serves 10.

title: oatmeal apple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets with Crisco. Cream Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla at medium speed 1 1/2 minutes.
Combine flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and salt. Beat into creamed mixture at low until well blended.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Stir in oats.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 13 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: bean and cheese enchiladas
directions: Mix and heat all ingredients together.
Put in soft shells and place in baking dish and top with grated cheese.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Pick one quart of the sheep or sour sarrell leaves and wash thoroughly. Clip off the ends of stems and place the remainder of the leaves into an unbaked pie crust. Cut one stick of butter into thin slices onto the leaves in the pan. Cover with 3/4 cup sugar and bake at 325° for about 30 to 40 minutes. Can put strips of pastry over top.

title: a peach of a dessert
directions: Reserve peach juice.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press firmly into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.
Gradually beat in milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread evenly over crumb crust.
Top with peaches. Chill.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Put in casserole.
Place biscuits on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: watergate cake with cover up frosting
directions: Blend all of the ingredients together - beat for two minutes. Grease and flour three 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into loaf in baking loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: This slaw to be made hot.
Heat sugar, oil, vinegar and salt. Sprinkle the cut up or shredded vegetables into the celery seed. Pour over cut up vegetables the heated sugar, oil, vinegar and salt while still warm.
Let stand until cool, then stir, refrigerate until ready to serve.
This keeps for several days, and is better the second day.

title: chicken, cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts. Leave whole or chop. Cook rice.
Saute onions; combine broccoli, cheese, onion soup and rice. Add chicken if chopped; if left whole, place chicken in oblong baking dish and pour rice mixture over top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Frost with Rich's Whip.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: Saute carrots, celery, onion in margarine.
Add chicken broth. Simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add potato soup and cheese.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring often so cheese does not sink to the bottom and stick.
Add sour cream just before serving.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together; mix into shortening and sugars.
Add coconut and flavoring.
Roll dough into small balls and dip tops in water and then in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: puerto rican black bean soup
directions: Measure 1/4 cup black beans; set aside for garnish.
In food processor bowl with metal blade or in blender container, combine beans, chicken broth, water, onion, garlic, cumin and oregano leaves.
Process until smooth.
Transfer mixture to medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place in serving bowls.
Garnish with reserved black beans, chopped bell pepper and sour cream. Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: macaroni with ricotta cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender; drain and return to pot.
Mix Ricotta and parsley until smooth.
Add to macaroni with butter.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Serve hot and sprinkle with cheese.

title: gift of the magi bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter or margarine with sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with mashed bananas.
Stir in mandarin oranges, chocolate chips, coconuts, 1/2 cup almonds and cherries.
Pour into 2 greased 7 1/2 x 3 3/4-inch loaf pans. Sprinkle remainder of almonds over tops.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
When cool, sieve confectioners sugar over tops. Makes 2 loaves.

title: souper scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and onion in 9-inch glass dish.
Pour soup, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese and margarine; bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered. Remove cover and brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Pour jello over cream cheese. Pour 1 cup boiling water over cheese and jello. Let cool. Add oranges and pineapple. Add Cool Whip.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute each kind of seafood in a small amount of butter and seasoned salt until cooked and put into large double boiler.
Add milk, cream, clam juice, pepper and more seasoned salt to taste. Heat to simmering.
Best if cooled and reheated a couple of times.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Butterscotch chips may be used in place of chocolate chips.

title: big monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, peanut butter, vanilla and corn syrup.
Beat well.
Add oats, soda, salt, chips and M&M's. Drop by 1/4 cup 4 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: grandma's peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Pour fruit and juice into butter.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over top of mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Layer as follows: browned meat (do not need to brown ham); crumbled bread; cheese; eggs and milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 2 quart greased casserole dish.

title: hot dogs in sauce
directions: Put currant jelly and mustard in electric skillet and warm. Cut hog dogs into bite size pieces.
Mix and simmer.
You may also use bologna or Hickory Farms bologna.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oats to butter and boiling water.
Let sit for 2 minutes. Add the eggs, sugars, flour, cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: broccoli pasta salad
directions: Cut up broccoli into small to medium size pieces (throw away thick part of stalk).
Boil 4 cups of water and add 1/2 teaspoon salt when boiling.
Add broccoli and cook to taste (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).
Drain broccoli, reserving a cup of water.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, undrained fruit cocktail, 1 cup coconut and eggs.
Blend and beat 2 minutes on medium speed and pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Bring butter, sugar and milk to boil and boil 1 minute.
Stir remaining coconut.
Spoon over warm cake. Top with whipped topping if desired.
Real good.

title: baked eggplant napoli
directions: In a skillet, saute chopped onions in peanut oil.
Add tomato puree, water, salt, oregano and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly and beat in one egg at a time until all four are added.
Sift flour with baking powder, alternately adding flour and ending with flour.
Vanilla and lemon can be added to the milk.
For layer cake, bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
For cupcakes bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: roquefort cheese balls
directions: Cream the cheeses.
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce, parsley and brandy.
Mix well and chill for 1 hour.
Roll in chopped nuts and freeze.

title: gian-mikel's grilled chicken breasts
directions: Trim fat from chicken breasts and slice in half.
Add some fresh herbs to taste such as thyme, basil, oregano, garlic powder, salt, pepper, olive oil and vinegar.
Mix everything, making sure breasts are well coated.
Marinate for at least 1 hour.
Grill and serve hot.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas.
Let sit for 2 hours.
Add sliced bananas.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Mix 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt and oregano. In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1 cup sauce, 3 noodles and 1/2 cup cheese mix.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Pour water around edges of pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Mix soup with milk and
rice.
Pour
into
11 1/2 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Lightly
salt
and
pepper chicken pieces and place in mixture.
Sprinkle
with dry soup mix.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until done.

title: yummy turtle brownies
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 pan or cover pan with foil (for thick brownies), or use jelly roll pan lined with foil (for thinner brownies).
Combine 1/3 cup evaporated milk with the caramels in small saucepan, heat low to medium, stirring constantly to avoid burning or scorching, turn down to low heat to keep warm.
Combine dry cake mix with 2/3 cup of evaporated milk and nuts, stir by hand until dough holds together; press half of dough mixture in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350 F for 6 minutes.
remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over top, pour caramel mixture over chips.
Spread remaining cake mixture over top of caramel. Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Let cool completely before slicing into pieces.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and blend well.
Stir in milk and broth.
Cook over medium heat and stir constantly.
Prepare rice. Add rice to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add olives and broil 1 minute.

title: barbecue chex mix
directions: Stir all together. Mix oil, powder and sauce. Coat cereal, pretzels and peanuts. Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: cottage cheese fluff
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with cottage cheese.
Drain fruit well.
Fold in cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate two hours before serving.

title: turkey or chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Transfer to large baking dish.
Add all ingredients, mixing well.
Additional cheese is optional, but you can sprinkle more cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Good for leftover turkey after Thanksgiving.

title: banana pops
directions: Break the bananas into chunks and place in a small bowl.
Mash thoroughly with a fork, then add the peanut butter and honey and blend well.
Place in ice tups set.
Seal and freeze.
Makes 6.

title: asparagus medley
directions: In wok or skillet, heat oil. Add asparagus, zucchini, onions and celery. Cook, stirring frequently, 4 to 5 minutes until crisp-tender. Add water chestnuts, pimiento, soy sauce, sugar and pepper. Stir until heated through.

title: tortilla pie
directions: Brown meat; add onions, seasonings, tomato sauce and taco sauce.
Cook until thick like spaghetti sauce.
Add corn.
This makes up the sauce layer.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt butter and mix with crushed cookies.
Press in the bottom of Tupperware pie taker.
Soften ice cream and spread over crumbs. Soften hot fudge and pour over ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip on top and decorate with cookies or chocolate curls.
Freeze for 2 hours.

title: curried baked fruit
directions: Combine butter, sugar and curry powder.
Pour sauce over fruit (in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish).
Bake 60 minutes at 325°.

title: swiss quiche
directions: Mix cheese and flour.
Layer broccoli, ham, onions and cheese into pie shell.
Repeat layers.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture in pie shell.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 2 heaping teaspoonfuls in a cup.
Fill cup with hot water.
Enjoy!

title: baked apple butter
directions: Cut apples into quarters (no need to peel or core).
Cook apple quarters until done.
Put through a colander or mill to remove seeds.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.
Stir every now and then.
Put in jars and seal.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Bake at 350°.
Use favorite filling or icing.

title: sally's coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and add chopped green pepper and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, celery seed and sugar.
Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep for up to 1 week.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Shape into a ball.
Roll the ball in the nuts.
Prepare 1 day before serving.

title: crab stuffed celery
directions: Combine together tossing lightly.
Spoon into celery ribs. Cut diagonally into serving pieces.
Makes 28 servings.

title: raisin clusters
directions: Yields 2 dozen.
In medium glass bowl, heat chocolate at Medium-low 3 to 4 minutes or until chocolate is melted; stir in milk until smooth, then raisins.
To complete, drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased wax paper lined cookie sheets; chill.

title: sugar 'n' spice nuts
directions: Place nuts in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, beat egg white and orange juice with a fork until foamy.
Add sugar, orange peel, cinnamon, ginger and allspice; mix well.
Pour over nuts and stir to coat.
Spread into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 275°, stirring every 15 minutes, for 45 minutes.

title: apple raisin tapioca
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil.
Mix tapioca and sugar.
Add to water, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes or until tapioca is not quite clear.
Remove from heat.
Mix the remaining ingredients in large buttered baking dish.
Pour the tapioca over the apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are soft.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: In a large saucepan, combine egg yolks, water, vinegar and salt. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and reaches 160°. Remove from heat and cool. Fold in whipped cream.

title: super easy stew
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot with cover.
Bake in oven at 325° for 3 hours.
Do not open during cooking.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: oriental pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 5 hours. Pour over meat and marinate at least 24 hours.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, vinegar and salt. Put in blender. Slowly add oil in blender. Stir in grated onion and poppy seed. Serve over mixed fruit.

title: italian salad bowl
directions: Combine lettuce, romaine, zucchini, radishes, mushrooms and green onions.
Season with salt and pepper.
Toss lightly with dressing and sprinkle Blue cheese over top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: high energy soup
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.

title: spicy cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and cut lengthwise in two.
With small spoon, scrape out seeds leaving hollow like shell boats.
Cut cucumbers crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
In small glass bowl, combine soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, sesame seed oil, Tabasco and salt and mix well. Add cucumbers.
With large spoon, toss to coat each slice. Chill before serving.
Serves 4.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls and flatten a bit. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 325° oven until bottoms of cookies get brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when cool.
Roll 2 or 3 times in powdered sugar.
These cookies should be put on brown paper to cool when removed from oven.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add the shortening and work to make fine crumbs.
Stir in the raisins, currants and caraway seeds.
Stir in buttermilk.
Turn dough into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Spread evenly and bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook meat and drain. Add soups and corn; cook a few minutes. Cook noodles.
Pour mixture over noodles. Add half of the cheese and bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Spread rest of cheese over top while hot.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add butter, sugar, syrup, vanilla, salt, flour and pecans.
Pour into pie shell (9-inch pie will be full). Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until center is soft or set. Enjoy.

title: city-slicker apple sticks
directions: Stir-fry sausage until crunchy.
Set aside.
Cut up apple, cook, strain and set aside.
Mix together dry ingredients, then stir in drained sausage and apple.
Add beaten egg, milk and butter.
Stir and pour into muffin tins or corn tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
To serve, use 2 teaspoons of mixture for each cup of boiling water.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Put chips with wax in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate.

title: galaxy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar, vanilla and a few drops of food coloring.
Work in flour and salt until dough holds together.
(If dough is dry, mix in 1 to 2 tablespoons light cream.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes in a greased casserole dish.
Cover with onions.
Break up raw hamburger on top of potatoes and onions. Mix soups, corn and milk.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bacon and cheddar chicken
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble. Leave about 3 tablespoons grease in pan.
Dip chicken in egg and then bread crumbs to coat.
Saute in hot drippings 4 to 5 minutes on medium heat until golden brown on both sides.
When chicken is nearly cooked, top with cheese.
Cover for 30 seconds until cheese melts.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: "seven minute" frosting
directions: Mix together all ingredients except vanilla. Beat over boiling water until mixture stands in soft peaks, 7 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Beat until very thick. Spread on cake.

title: picnic spice layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour with soda, baking powder, salt, spices and cocoa.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with applesauce.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: mounds bars
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine. Put into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Spread with flaked coconut. Pour condensed milk over graham cracker crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add soup and milk.
Blend.
Add Cheez Whiz; simmer until melted.
Add broccoli, rice and salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add chicken, Ro-Tel and Velveeta.
Dip tortillas in pan of melted butter and spoon on mixture.
Roll tortilla.
Place tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
If any mixture is left, pour on top of tortillas.
Add sour cream on top; bake for about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Bring the mixture to a boil and let it boil about five minutes (or to the soft ball stage).
Remove from the heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Immediately drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let set to cool.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix and store in a tightly covered jar.
Add 2 tablespoons per cup of boiling water.

title: cheese pie
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix soup, both milks, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese and butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: festive fudge-filled bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease jelly-roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inches).
Mix first 6 ingredients in large bowl; stir in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining mixture in pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: brown sugar toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line an 8 inch square pan with foil, and lightly grease.
In large bowl beat together for 3 minutes with an electric mixer the sugar, flour, butter, eggs, and vanilla. Spread in pan and sprinkle with toffee.
Bake 25 minutes.
Lift foil by ends to cutting board after cool, and cut into bars.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix together, cook for 1 hour.
Serve with grated cheese and Tostitos.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone; set aside.
Saute two onions in butter.
Add Velveeta cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes and all the soups. Melt together.
Do not dilute soups.
In a large baking pan place a layer of chips, thin layer of chicken, layer of soup mixture and repeat until a layer of soup on top.
Top with grated cheese.

title: stuffed baked sweet potatoes
directions: Bake until tender.
Cool potatoes; cut in half.
Scoop out pulp from 8 halves.
Discard the skins.
Scoop out the pulp from the remaining 8 halves.
Leave 1/4-inch to make a shell.
Beat all the pulp.
Add orange juice, butter, salt and cinnamon.
Fill shells; sprinkle 1 tablespoon butter and 1 teaspoon brown sugar over each shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Drain off excess grease. Add sauce, paste, green beans and corn.
Put in pan.
Top with mashed potatoes.

title: orange cheese pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold milk in blender; let stand a while. Add boiling milk; cover and process at low speed.
Stop blender; add sugar, salt, cottage cheese and undiluted concentrate.
Cover and process at high speed.
Chill until mixture is thick and mounds slightly.
Turn into crumb crust.
Chill 4 hours.
Serve with sliced strawberries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Prepare in layers in the following order in rectangular PLASTIC container:

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients in bowl; pour over entire loins. Sprinkle more flakes on top, if desired (some people prefer less pepper flakes).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients and bring to boil for about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter, salt, vanilla and quick oats.
Drop onto waxed paper by spoonfuls.

title: how to feed sourdough starter
directions: Put initial starter in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.
Mix ingredients well and add to starter.
Let stand out of refrigerator all day (8 to 12 hours).
Take 1 cup out to use in making bread.
Return remaining starter to refrigerator.
Feed again in 3 to 5 days.
Starter must be fed 2 times before making bread.
This is to increase bulk.

title: hot pot recipe
directions: Heat oil in skillet and brown meat all over.
Put in oven-safe pan.
Brown vegetables in skillet.
Add to meat along with mushrooms and garlic.
Sprinkle the flour over any fat or juices in the pan.
Stir and cook before gradually adding the stock.
Bring to a boil.
Season well and pour over meat.
Cover and cook in oven slowly at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Thicken gravy, if necessary, before serving.
Good served over rice or noodles.

title: goulash
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients together and cook until browned, then cook macaroni separately.
Drain and mix with hamburger mixture.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Cut
steak; flour them and brown steak in oil.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Top with onion and mushrooms.
Combine water, garlic and steak sauce; pour over vegies.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: north stars
directions: Bake bread as directed on package. You can also cut bread in design if desired, or you can use mini rye bread bought at store in bakery section.
Cool baked bread.
Combine cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and Italian dressing mix.
Slice bread into thin slices.
Drop about 1 teaspoon of mixture on bread slices. Sprinkle with both red and green peppers.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly crisp.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add the zucchini, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Pour in greased and floured pans.
Cook in preheated oven at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut off and discard wing tips. Cut each wing into 2 sections. Place chicken on the unseated rack of a boiler pan. Broil 4-5 inches form the heat about 10 minutes or until chicken is browned., turning once. Transfer chicken to a 4 quart cooker. Combine chilli sauce and hot pepper sauce, pour over wings. Cover and cook on low heat for 4-5 hours or high heat 2-2 1/2 hours. Serve chicken with Ranch salad dressing. Makes 32 appetizers.

title: easy chocolate eclair squares
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package, using 1/2 cup less milk.
After it sets up, fold in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer approximately 1/3 of crackers, covering completely.
Cover crackers with 1/2 of cream mixture. Repeat layers.
Top with remaining crackers, covering completely.
Melt chocolate, butter and milk over low heat or in microwave.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add powdered sugar, mixing until well blended.
Spread over crackers.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and drain.
Fry onions and celery in butter. Mix cheese into hot rice.
Mix in broccoli and then soups and fried celery and onions and then mix all together.
Bake in casserole dish at 425° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: self-rising flour rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar and yeast.
Let stand a few minutes.
Stir; add oil.
Stir well.
Add flour; let rise.
Make out rolls.
Use same flour, if needed, to roll out.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 400° until light brown, 10 to 20 minutes.

title: cake icing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
If too soft, add a little sugar.
If too hard, add a little milk.

title: greek salad
directions: Marinate in Good Seasons Italian dressing (the one you make from a package, oil and vinegar).
Marinate overnight.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: micro-quick potato sticks
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut into 8 lengthwise spears.
Spray potato spears with cooking spray.
In plastic bag, combine cheese, oregano, paprika and garlic powder.
Add potatoes a few at a time and shake to coat.
Spray microwave-safe dish with cooking spray. Arrange potatoes in single layer.
Microwave on High 8 to 12 minutes.
Rotate 1/2 way through cooking time.

title: all-in-one hamburger casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Mix ground beef with onion and spread in bottom.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and chili powder. Sprinkle 1/3 mixture over hamburger; dot with 1/2 tablespoon butter.
Measure 1 cup rice and spread in even layer over hamburger.
Repeat flour mixture and butter as before.
Make a layer of tomatoes, including liquid.
Repeat flour mixture and butter.
Spread corn on top and dot with butter.
Cover and bake in 350°
oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix everything together with a mixture of the mayo and sour cream. Crab meat can be substituted.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
After it gets done, rinse well and set aside. Melt butter in saucepan until melted and liquid.
Blend flour in butter until it becomes a paste.
Add milk to that, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Once thickened, remove from heat. Cut cheese up and place in sauce.
(Note:
If sauce thickens too much, just add a little milk to thin it out.)
Stir cheese into sauce until the cheese starts to melt.
Then add in salt to taste. Get your casserole bowl and layer the bottom of the bowl with the sauce first.
Then add macaroni.
Continue alternating.
The last layer should be the sauce.
Bake at 450 degrees for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: haystacks
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add only enough barbecue sauce to moisten beef.
Spray muffin cups with Pam.
Flatten biscuits and press into muffin cups.
Fill with beef mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake according to biscuit directions.

title: plantation chili
directions: Brown meat with 1 cup onion and 1 teaspoon chili powder. Drain tomatoes well; break apart with hand and add to meat mixture.
Add garlic and remainder of chili powder and onion. After cooking 1/2 half, add peppers.
Add salt to taste.

title: pineapple chunks in ginger ale
directions: Amounts of each is personal choice.
Fill parfait or sherbet glasses with chilled, drained pineapple chunks.
Pour over ginger ale (any amount you like).
Add a dash of whipped cream or Cool Whip!

title: california mix vegetable casserole
directions: Place frozen vegetables in greased baking dish.
Heat soup and add drained mushrooms, milk, rice and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy yogurt jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add yogurt and stir until almost liquified.
Add cold water.
"Float" mini marshmallows on top as desired.
Chill for 3 hours and enjoy!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add oatmeal and nuts and stir.
Make into drop cookies and cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Pour over apples.
Let set while mixing the dry ingredients. Mix dry ingredients into apple mixture. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost cake with Philadelphia Cream Icing.

title: summer squash casserole(yellow squash)
directions: Layer ingredients into a buttered 2-quart baking dish, ending with crackers and margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.
(I like to sprinkle garlic powder over each layer.)

title: corn pie
directions: Cook chicken; cool and save broth.
Put half of cut corn into bottom of casserole or baking dish, then a layer of boned chicken, a layer of sliced egg, salt and pepper.
Repeat these layers, using all ingredients.
Pour chicken broth over all until casserole is half filled.
Cover with pastry or biscuit dough. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: white chili bistro
directions: Cook over medium heat until soft the onion, minced garlic and vegetable oil.
Add ground cumin and cook 5 minutes.
Add cubed turkey and ground turkey. Cook until meat isn't pink. Add pearl barley, chicken peas, jalapeno peppers, chicken broth, marjoram and dried savory. Cook 45 minutes.
Add arrowroot and cook 15 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with melted Monterey Jack cheese and sliced green onions on top.

title: baked corn
directions: Pour all of the ingredients into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Set in pan of hot water.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven until set and firm.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Combine broccoli, corn, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, egg, 1 tablespoon butter, salt, onion and pepper. Mix well. Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine 2 tablespoons melted butter and 1/4 cup cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over broccoli. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: white castle hamburgers
directions: Mix and fry the ground round, adding 1 teaspoon minced onion on top before you turn over; place buns on top to warm.

title: cherry-pineapple salad
directions: Remove rind from pineapple and cut into chunks.
Place pineapple in a shallow dish; sprinkle with sugar.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, drain pineapple.
Arrange pineapple and cherries on greens.
Drizzle dressing over fruit and sprinkle with Blue cheese.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Melt chocolate bits in double boiler.
Add vanilla, salt, butter and milk.
Blend well.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Remove from heat and mix well.
Pour into flat buttered pan.
Let stand overnight, but do not refrigeate.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, cream the butter and sugar. Add flour and vanilla.
Fold crushed potato chips into mixture. Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a skillet, melt 3 tablespoons butter over medium heat. Saute pepper and onion until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper; stir until well blended.
Gradually add milk; cook and stir until thickened.
Slowly blend in egg yolks.
Remove from the heat; fold in corn, pimentos and 1 cup crumbs.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining butter and toss with remaining crumbs; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking time. Rest 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, in a large bowl, mix all ingredients except 2 tablespoons catsup.
Firmly pat mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
To serve, pour off fat, invert onto a warm platter, and spoon 2 tablespoons catsup over top of meat loaf.
Garnish with parsley sprigs. Serves 8.

title: bagels
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine yeast and 1 3/4 cups flour. Combine water, sugar and salt. Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 1 1/2 minutes. Beat 3 minutes at high speed. By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough. Turn out on a
floured surface and knead until smooth. Cover for 15 minutes.

title: mullet baked in clay(6 servings)
directions: Wrap dressed mullet in leaves.
Roll in soft clay.
Bake in open fire or glowing coals.
When the clay is burned hard, break with a hammer and open carefully.
The mullet skin will adhere to the leaves and the fish may be removed intact.

title: pat's easy bake chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly; place in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with garlic salt, then grated cheese, with paprika on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 45 minutes to an hour, depending on how fast your oven heats.
Not only is this easy, but it tastes good!
When family members visit, they always request my "special" chicken.
The pan drippings make a great gravy!
(This is the first time I've ever shared the recipe.)

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Heat oven at 375°.
Lightly grease bottom and sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Mix crust together of graham crackers and margarine.
Pat onto bottom of pan and up the sides a little.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In large stock pot, brown onion in margarine.
Add carrots, celery, green beans and zucchini.
Wait 3 to 5 minutes.
Add water and remaining ingredients except for the noodles.
Let cook at a very slow boil for 3 hours.
Add tiny noodles at the last 20 minutes of cooking.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: susie's foolproof roast
directions: Rinse meat; place in roasting pan.
Surround the meat with the whole, peeled potatoes.
Cover the meat with the can of soup and sliced onions.
Pour 16 ounces of water around the meat.
Lightly sprinkle the entire contents with seasoned salt and pepper.
Cover with a lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
(There should be plenty of juice to make gravy.)

title: yeast rolls
directions: Heat milk and butter (warm not boiling).
Sprinkle yeast and sugar
in
flour.
Pour
milk and butter in flour and stir. Add eggs
and
stir.
Add
flour
as you knead, using enough to make a nice soft ball.
Let rise until double in size.
Shape. Let rise. Bake at 375° until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with potato chips and bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: breakfast tacos
directions: In frying pan, cook sausage and Potatoes O'Brien until sausage and potatoes are done.
Beat eggs and add to sausage mixture. Cook until eggs are done, mixing constantly.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant into cubes.
Cook in salt water until tender.
Line a baking dish with crackers.
Put alternate layers of crackers and eggplant.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup into which milk or cream is added.
Roll cracker crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until brown.

title: icing for pineapple cake
directions: Cook until thick.
Add 1 cup coconut.
Use pineapple cake mix and bake according to package directions.

title: tropical ice
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir well and freeze until firm. To serve, partially thaw fruit mixture.
Place in punch bowl and break into chunks.
Add ginger ale; stir until slushy.

title: strawberry frozen jam
directions: Boil for 1 minute and stir in fruit.
Stir for 3 minutes. Pour into jars and let it stand for 24 hours, then place in the freezer.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Mix together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in middle of pie comes out clean.

title: crab soup
directions: Boil vegetables and drain when soft.
Mash with potato masher. Beat eggs with milk.
Add to vegetables.
Add crab meat, Old Bay, seasonings and butter.
Simmer on low heat.
Do not boil.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic, onions and oregano, then add tomato soup, water and vinegar.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer lasagne noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Also use the meat sauce the same way.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; heat through.
Put a layer of Doritos in a greased casserole dish; top with chicken mixture and then add a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers until gone. Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Be sure all moisture is drained from thawed spinach.
Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise, vegetable soup mix and garlic powder.
Chop and add the green pepper, chestnuts and green onions.
Add spinach; mix well and refrigerate until serving.

title: rosy red plum cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Grease and flour Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from pan while hot.
With pastry brush, put on Lemon Glaze.

title: easy spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Will remain fresh up to 7 days.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until brown. Yield: 24 rolls.

title: tomato basil pasta salad
directions: Saute chicken in white wine.
Cut into small pieces.
Set aside.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces; set aside.
In large bowl, mix cooked pasta, cheese and chicken.
Add tomatoes and canola oil.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil.
Chill for approximately 1 hour before serving.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix the cake mix according to the directions on the package. Fill paper baking cups 2/3 full.
Cream the cheese with the sugar. Beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate pieces.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend sugar and cream cheese.
Add milk and peanut butter. Cream thoroughly.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust. Freeze until firm.

title: evelyn's refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
warm water.
Mix with the 2 tablespoons sugar and baking powder;
let stand 20 minutes.
Scald the	milk; add margarine, 2/3 cup sugar and salt.
Cool, then add
the beaten
eggs.
Combine
all
ingredients with 9 cups flour.
Just stir in;
batter will be thin.
Cover and refrigerate
overnight. Make
into	rolls
hours before serving. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: rock cornish hens
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Wash rice several times and add to boiling water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour without stirring until tender; drain if necessary.
Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Saute onions and mushrooms in melted butter until lightly browned.
Toss lightly with wild rice and American cheese.
Rinse hens with water and pat dry.
Rub cavity with salt.
Fill lightly with wild rice mixture.
To close cavity, sew or skewer and lace with cord.
Tie legs together.
Brush with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Roast, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serves 6.

title: crisscross peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking powder in a bowl.
Stir to mix. Combine peanut butter, margarine and fructose in a mixing bowl. Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and sweetener of your choice.
Gradually add the flour mixture.
Roll a teaspoon of dough into a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with a fork in a crisscross design.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly on cookie sheet, then move to cooling rack.

title: sour cream tacos
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with spray Pam. Break chips to cover bottom of dish (may not use entire bag). Brown beef and drain.
Add onion and pepper and saute.
Pour beef mixture over chips.
Combine melted Velveeta, Ro-Tel and sour cream and pour over beef.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and hot.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in pie shell and place in refrigerator until eaten.

title: chocolate maple nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt. Cut in margarine until crumbly. Stir in 1 beaten egg. Press firmly on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion.
Stir in soup and tomatoes. Add cheese, a little at a time, until it melts.
Serve with Fritos or Doritos corn chips.
Makes a large amount and recipe can be cut down.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients with a whisk or an electric mixer.
When smooth, add 1 bag of frozen small shrimp, thawed and deveined. Serve with Ruffles.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package and add butter.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Melt caramels and milk together.
Spoon caramel mixture over cake top. Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining batter overall and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish or pan.
Sift and measure flour.
Mix flour and sugar together in a bowl.
Add margarine.
Mix together with a fork or pastry blender until mixture looks crumbly. Open the peaches and drain off all the liquid.
Spread fruit evenly in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle crumb mixture evenly on top of fruit.
Bake 30-40 minutes. Topping should be golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Combine salsa, brown sugar and mustard together in a small bowl. Place chicken in a baking dish; pour sauce over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend together shortening, salt, grated lemon rind and sugar. Beat in egg and milk.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda to mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheet. Grease bottom of glass.
Dip glass in sugar and flatten each cookie.
Sprinkle cookie with nutmeg.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly golden.
Bake at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix. Add remaining ingredients, except M&M's, and mix until blended.
Dough will be stiff.
Stir with spoon the M&M's candies into the dough. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 7 to 10 minutes (bottoms will be light brown).
Oven should be preheated.
Remove from baking sheet and store in cookie jar.
Yields approximately 72 cookies.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Pour dressing over broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms and green onions and let set 45 minutes before serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine, brown sugar, sugar and eggs. Mix flour, baking soda, vanilla, butterscotch morsels, pecans, and potato chips. Make into 1 inch balls and place on cookie sheet about 1 inch apart. Bake at 350° for 7-10 minutes. Let cool in pan about 5 minutes then remove onto waxed paper with spatula to finish cooling.

title: barbecued mini meatballs
directions: Combine eggs, water and contents of pancake mix envelope.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add ground beef; mix lightly.
Shape small meatballs, using 1 rounded teaspoonful for each.
Arrange in single layer on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in 400° oven 10 to 15 minutes until done.
Add meatballs to barbecue sauce.
Can be served with toothpicks.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
Place in glass 7 x 12-inch baking dish. Microwave, loosely covered, on High for 3 minutes.
Rearrange meatballs.
Microwave for 5 to 7 minutes longer or until cooked through.
Let stand for 3 minutes; drain.
Blend brown sugar, vinegar and cornstarch in baking dish.
Stir in undrained pineapple and soy sauce.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir mixture.
Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in meatballs and green peppers.
Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until green pepper is tender-crisp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Wash and dry pork chops.
Place on waxed paper.
Salt and pepper on each side.
Place chops in foil lined baking pan.
Put a few dabs of ketchup about the size of a dime on each one.
Pour enough coca-cola to cover chops.
Cover with foil and seal.
Bake in 350 degrees oven for an hour or more depending on thickness of chops.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Sear pork chops on both sides until browned in skillet with no grease.
When chops are browned on one side, turn.
Add sliced ingredients.
Add tomato juice, a little more salt and pepper may be needed.
Lower heat to simmer and cook, covered, for 1 hour. Delightful served over rice.

title: cheese and jam loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in biscuit mix, egg and one tablespoon sugar.
Mix well.
Turn onto biscuit mix dusted surface.
Knead 20 times.
Place on center of greased 15 1/2 x 12-inch baking sheet.
Roll to a 14 x 9-inch rectangle.
Combine cream cheese, the 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Spread lengthwise down center third of rectangle.
Make 3-inch long cuts at 1-inch intervals on both long sides.
Fold strips at angles over filling.
Cover and chill overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Spoon jam down center of loaf.
Bake 5 minutes more. Serve warm.
Makes one loaf.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in one big bowl.
Place in baking dish and cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Fifteen minutes before it's ready, add topping of crushed corn flakes mixed with melted butter.
Serve golden brown.

title: troy aikman corn
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: In a small bowl mix together finely chopped nuts, 1/2 cup sugar and 6 tablespoons of butter.
Set this aside.
Grease an angel food pan and preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Cream together 1/4 lb of butter, 1 cup sugar.
Add in the eggs sour cream, flour, baking soda and powder, and vanilla.
When combined, pour 1/2 of the batter into the prepared angel food pan.
Top with the apple slices and more chopped nuts.
Add in the remaining batter.
Bake in oven at 375 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: bacon cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until tender but firm.
Drain and cube. In a bowl, mix potatoes with onion, cheese and mayonnaise.
Put into baking dish.
Sprinkle with bacon and olives.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken pieces and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brush mayonnaise all over chicken.
Dip chicken in bread crumbs until coated.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: stuffed rolled meat loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend ground ham, ground pork, crackers, egg, milk, salt, thyme and pepper.
Mix well.
Moisten a piece of waxed paper, 18 inches long.
Pat meat mixture to make a rectangle, 9 x 12 inches.
Spread onions over top of meat evenly. Coarsely chop the drained apricots.
Sprinkle over onions. Sprinkle parsley over all.
Roll as for a jelly roll, starting with a 9-inch side, making a compact roll.
Simply lift up the waxed paper to start meat rolling.
Place meat roll in lightly greased 9 x 5-inch bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit pudding *
directions: Pour batter mixture into greased baking dish; pour fruit mixture over batter.
Spread margarine on top and cook in oven at 400° for about 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.
May be served with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 12 cup muffin pan. Combine dry ingredients with pastry blender.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in nuts, cracker crumbs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into well buttered 9-inch pie pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 35 minutes.
Cool.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Fold in pineapple topping and spread on pie. Chill.

title: jelly bellies
directions: Beat margarine until soft.
Gradually add brown sugar; continue beating until well blended.
Blend in egg, molasses and vanilla.
Add oats, flour and coconut, mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Indent tops of cookies with floured finger.
Fill indentation with jelly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: country club eggs
directions: Place bread, cheese and ham or sausage in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat eggs; add milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread mixture. Drizzle melted margarine over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Complete breakfast!!

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add to mixture. Makes 1 loaf pan or 9 x 13 pan. Will be thin. Bake at 350° for 35
minutes or until done.

title: baked deviled orange roughy(yields 4 servings)
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Cut fillets into 6 serving size portions.
Arrange fillets in a single layer in a greased shallow baking pan.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese, mayo, milk, onion soup mix, lemon juice, tarragon and mustard.
Spread cream cheese mixture atop fillets.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish almost flakes with a fork.
Meanwhile, combine bread crumbs, parsley, Parmesan cheese and paprika; sprinkle atop filets. Bake 3 to 4 minutes more or until crumbs are golden and fish flakes easily with a fork.
Enjoy!

title: old fashioned custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake about 40 minutes or until knife inserted into side comes out clean.
Center is soft but will set later.
Bake in hot 450° oven for first 15 minutes.
Then reduce to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add the beaten egg yolks the cocoa and the mashed potatoes.

Alternate the milk and flour in which the baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon have been sifted together, having reserved 1/4 cup of flour for the nut meats. Fold in floured nuts and the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into buttered and floured cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Line the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crumbs and melted oleo. Mash down evenly.
Beat eggs with sticks of oleo and sugar in electric mixer at least 15 minutes.
Spread over crumb crust and cover with sliced bananas.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas, and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans and cut-up cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup over top.

title: spinach cheese casserole
directions: Drain spinach well, squeeze with paper towel.
Butter deep casserole dish or 2 more shallow casserole dishes.
Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Bake at 325°
to 350° approximately 1 hour or until edges bubble and brown slightly.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift flour; measure and sift with salt, soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Cover; chill for 1 hour.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut and place on greased cookie sheet.
Dip the bottom of a drinking glass in water and then in sugar and press cookie balls flat.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 10 minutes.

title: appe-teaser cheese cracker cake
directions: Brush a 9-inch spring-form pan with the melted butter.
Pat cracker crumbs on bottom and sides, reserving 1/2 cup for later use.
Set aside.
Don't use the tube part of the spring-form pan.

title: aunt mary's quick hot rolls
directions: Stir sugar, salt and butter into scalded milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk mixture, egg and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make soft dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Punch down and shape into rolls.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put cheese on top and bake for 5 minutes.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Remove rolls from pan.
Split lengthwise and replace bottom half in pan.
Combine butter, Worcestershire sauce, onion and mustard.
Boil for 1 minute.
Layer ham and cheese on rolls. Spoon 1/3 of sauce over cheese.
Top with rolls and spoon remaining sauce over top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix with spoon with 1/3 cup milk, nuts (chopped) and melted margarine.
Batter will be thick.
Spread 1/2 batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch loaf cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 6 minutes. While this is baking, melt caramels in bowl with 1/3 cup milk.
I melt mine in microwave.
Stir every minute or so until all caramels are melted.
Remove cake from oven; spread melted caramels over all.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over all.
Drop rest of cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: jessie grant's applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan 2 hours at 275°.
Let cake cool before removing from pan.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Mix in sugars, egg, peanut butter, margarine and shortening until smooth.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes. Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough by teaspoonfuls into 2 1/2-inch fingers on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, about 8 minutes; cool.
Dip one end of each cookie into Cocoa Glaze. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place uncooked rice in bottom of casserole dish.	Add corn on top of rice.
Place one 8 ounce can tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water on top of corn.	Add onions on top of liquid.
Place green pepper on onions.
Spread ground beef to cover green peppers.
Pour on 8 ounce can of tomato sauce with 1/4 cup water.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and bake 1 hour. Uncover bake 30 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Day 1:
Mix marshmallows and pineapple in covered bowl overnight.
Mix pineapple juice, beaten egg, sugar, flour and vinegar.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly until thick. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.

title: (mild) cheese cake
directions: Combine sugar, gelatine, salt, milk and egg yolk.
Cook (stirring constantly) until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Blend in cream cheese and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Chill until thick but not set, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken creole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow dish, mixing well. Dredge chicken in flour mixture, shaking off excess flour. Set chicken aside. Cook chicken in hot oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat about 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Remove chicken. Add onion, green pepper and garlic to Dutch oven; saute 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Add chicken, tomatoes, chicken broth and rice, stirring well. Cover and simmer 40 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed, stirring. Add okra. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
Melt margarine in nonstick saucepan (large).
Mix in cubed cheese (Velveeta); melt.
Add cooked macaroni and evaporated milk.
Turn into casserole dish.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Recipe can be halved.)

title: fresh blueberry sauce(microwave)
directions: Place all ingredients in a large glass bowl. Stir to blend. Lightly cover bowl with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until mixture boils.
Microwave at a simmer for an additional 5 minutes.
Let cool. Store in a covered jar in the refrigerator. This thickens as it cools.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: white bean and salsa dip
directions: In a blender or food processor, puree white kidney beans.
Then add all other ingredients EXCEPT picante sauce and shredded cheese. Process until smooth.
Transfer to a small flat bottom container, spread evenly in the bottom of the dish.
Pour enough picante sauce over the bean mixture to cover.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over picante sauce.
Serve dip with tortilla chips or corn chip scoops.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and shortening in large mixing bowl, until fluffy. Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, creaming well after each addition. Stir in vanilla, lemon extract and juice.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir thoroughly after each addition. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 15 minutes on wire rack; remove from pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine
all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Refrigerate until firm
enough to handle.
Form into a ball.	Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Combine molasses and baking soda.
Add to first mixture and stir well.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add to mixture alternately with the water.
Pour into a greased 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and place in greased, 3-quart casserole dish.
Layer chicken over the broccoli.

title: meatballs with onions(dawood basha)
directions: Put meat through a meat grinder twice.
Season the ground meat and knead it with your hands.
Shape into one-inch balls and set aside.
Brown the meatballs in oil.
Drain and set aside.
Peel the onions and saute in the remaining oil until golden.
Drain. Place the meatballs and onions in a saucepan with the water, seasoning and lemon juice.
Bring to the boil.
Reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Brown the flour in half a cup of water, stirring constantly.
Add the dissolved flour to the meat.
Crush the garlic with the dried mint and add to the meat a few minutes before serving.
Serve hot with boiled rice.

title: brandy alexander frappes
directions: Refrigerate 4 to 6 wine glasses several hours.
Soften ice cream.
Put in blender with brandy and creme de cacao.
Beat on high speed until smooth.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Mix and bring to a boil the sugar, corn syrup and peanut butter.
Add chocolate chips and spread on top.
Pat in a lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: best play dough
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil, dissolving the salt. While hot, add the next three ingredients.
The dough will be very lumpy.
Knead until smooth, approximately 5 minutes.
Store in plastic.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add water and cocoa.
Bring to boil. Mix together in large bowl the rest of the ingredients.
Pour liquid mixture over flour mixture and blend well.
Spread on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown ground beef until it loses its redness.
Remove ground beef from skillet.
You need 3 tablespoons of drippings.
(Add oil or shortening if needed.)
Add to it the bell pepper, onion and elbow macaroni.
Cook until macaroni turns yellow.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until macaroni is tender.

title: chicken livers with bacon
directions: Wrap pieces of bacon around each liver.
Secure with toothpick.
Fry in deep fat fryer at 350° until bacon is crisp, 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain and serve hot.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop onions and peppers fine.
Combine all vegetables and mix with salt.
Let stand overnight.
The next morning, drain well. Combine sugar, spices and vinegar.
Bring to boiling point and simmer about 20 minutes.
Add drained vegetables and simmer to desired consistency.
Remove spice bag.
Pack into hot jars and seal.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Thicken like white gravy.
Put on homemade butter biscuit and eat.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade sweet rolls
directions: Let bread dough thaw, then roll out dough to a large rectangle.
Brush on melted butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together; sprinkle over batter.
Roll up dough lengthwise.
Cut off slices about 1-inch thick; let rise in pan until just about double in size.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.
Top with favorite frosting.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.

title: cali's steamed clams
directions: While running under water, using a metal brush, scrub clams free of sand using a metal brush. Using a steamer or saucepot, heat water to boiling (must be enough water to cover clams). Cover steamer with tight fitting lid. Reduce heat to a lower temperature and steam clams until they open (about 6-11 minutes).

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Combine sugar, corn, salt and pepper.
Add the egg and mix well.
Add margarine to the milk in a pan and heat until margarine melts.
Blend with corn mixture.
Pour into a greased one quart casserole dish and place in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: frito salad
directions: Chop onion and bell pepper.
Drain cans of kidney beans and add to onion and bell pepper.
Add shredded cheese, Fritos and Catalina dressing.
Mix thoroughly.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat egg yolks and add to butter.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Flour fruits and nuts with dry ingredients.
Add remainder of flour to mixture.
Beat egg whites; add to all ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 225° for 4 hours.

title: onion burgers
directions: Blend ground beef with cottage cheese, egg and salt.
Divide into four portions and shape into large patties.
Heat margarine in skillet.
Add onions; saute over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from pan; keep warm.
Saute patties 2 to 3 minutes on each side or is done to your taste and liking.
Add onions back to pan to reheat.
Divide onions between meat patties.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crush croutons into small pieces. Generously spread with knife both sides of chicken with mustard and then sour cream.
Then cover chicken with croutons and place in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, with aluminum foil for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and increase temperature of oven to 450°.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.
Hope you enjoy!

title: mock pate de foie gras
directions: Saute mushrooms in a little butter until slightly brown.
Do not dry out.
Blend mushrooms, liver and butter and then add brandy.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Butter will rise to the top of crock and form a thin covering for the pate.

title: sweet 'n sour smoked sausage
directions: Slice sausage into chunks.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole and bake one hour at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles with picks for a delicious appetizer.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onions until transparent. Add mushrooms, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add Ragu sauce to mixture.
Simmer while making cream sauce.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Seed peppers and cook in boiling salt water for 5 minutes. Drain and place, cut side up, in shallow baking dish.
Combine beef, rice, milk, onion, egg and 1/4 cup tomato sauce. Mix well and put in peppers.
Pour rest of tomato sauce over peppers.
Dot each with butter. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in rice while hot.
Mix all the other ingredients with rice and bake in casserole dish 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Add flour and margarine; melt it all together into sauce.
Add tuna fish chunks, 1 can cream of mushroom soup, minced onion and curry powder.
Boil noodles and drain.
Place a layer of noodles in baking dish and a layer of sauce; continue until all used up. Spread 1 slice loaf bread on top, then add grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Save 1/2 can of onion rings to sprinkle on top of casserole before baking.
Boil chicken until tender; cut into small pieces. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, then put into large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until soup bubbles.

title: dressing for salads
directions: Mix well.
Do not refrigerate.
Pour as needed over salad and marinate about 1 hour.

title: teen time chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring just to boil on medium heat.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Blend next 4 ingredients.
With electric mixer on low, beat eggs into butter mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
With wooden spoon, stir in chocolate and nuts.
Spread into a greased and floured 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes; cool.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from bone. Cut into small pieces.
Place in ungreased casserole dish.
Add cream of chicken soup and chicken broth.
Melt butter.
Add to flour and milk, stir until smooth.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until it forms a crust and is golden brown.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat eggs well; add other ingredients.
Pour in gallon jug and shake.
Place in freezer and shake every hour.
Keep slushy.
Can be frozen and thawed.
Drop couple pieces of peppermint in bottom of glass.
Pour beverage on top.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add undrained pinto beans and the dry enchilada sauce and water.
In cake or lasagne pan, layer bean mixture, cheese, then 2 to 3 flour tortillas and continue in that order until all used.
Top layer should be the bean mixture and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy apple crisp
directions: Place apple pie filling in shallow 1-quart baking dish.
In a bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, salt and spices.
Add butter and mix well.
Spread topping evenly over pie filling.
Bake in 375° oven about 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: charlie miner's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients until blended.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 50 minutes.
Do not overbake!!!!!!

title: lime pie
directions: Bake pie shell according to directions on package; let cool.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine cranberries, raisins, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and water in a large saucepan.
Cook 15 minutes, until berries pop and mixture thickens.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Mix vinegar, mustard and sour cream together and combine with other ingredients.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Prepare spinach according to directions on package.
Drain well.
Cut stems from mushrooms; saute stems and caps in small amount of butter until browned.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Line shallow 10-inch casserole dish with spinach.
Add salt, onion and melted butter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Arrange mushrooms over cheese.
Season with garlic salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Fold edges of spinach over top.
(Spinach won't cover whole dish on top.)
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted and lightly brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash and quarter 4 pounds of apples.
Cook slowly until soft in 2 cups of cider.
Put through strainer.
Add to each cup of pulp 1/2 cup brown sugar.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in hot water.
Add lemon juice; add sugar, then pineapple juice.
